Name: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 atmos Undermycar Pepper
Description: Japan’s atmos teams up with South Korean brand Undermycar on the ASICS GEL Kayano 14 ‘Pepper Black,’ featuring a dark olive mesh upper with grey synthetic overlays and black side stripes. ASICS branding adorns the tongue and sockliner, while a decorative metal plate marked with Undermycar and atmos logos can be attached to the upper eyelet. The lifestyle runner sits atop a lightweight EVA midsole with visible GEL cushioning in the forefoot and heel.

Name: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Unaffected Infinite Wonders Pack Green
Description: Dropping as part of the collaborative ‘Infinite Wonders Pack,’ the UNAFFECTED x ASICS GEL Kayano 14 ‘Posy Green’ celebrates the 30th anniversary of the vaunted GEL Kayano franchise. A revised toggle lacing system secures the upper, crafted from dark green mesh with glossy synthetic overlays in black and Bottle Green. In addition to co-branded sockliners, the lateral heel of each shoe displays mismatched ‘UNAFFECTED’ and ‘GEL Kayano 14’ branding. The lifestyle runner is mounted on a lightweight EVA midsole with GEL cushioning for improved comfort and impact protection.

Name: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Unaffected Infinite Wonders Pack Black Silver
Description: The UNAFFECTED x ASICS GEL Kayano 14 ‘Dark Shadow’ is taken from the ‘Infinite Wonders Pack,’ a three-piece footwear collection designed in partnership with the South Korean brand. A toggle lacing system secures the upper, built with dark grey mesh and synthetic overlays in black and metallic silver. Dual branding appears on the insoles, while ‘UNAFFECTED’ and ‘GEL Kayano 14’ are stamped on the lateral heel of each shoe. The lifestyle runner rests on a lightweight EVA midsole with visible GEL cushioning in the forefoot and heel.

Name: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Unaffected Infinite Wonders Pack White
Description: Launching as part of the collaborative ‘Infinite Wonders Pack,’ the UNAFFECTED x ASICS GEL Kayano 14 ‘Bright White’ updates the lifestyle runner with a modified design inspired by the great outdoors. Toggle lacing secures the upper, crafted from white mesh with tonal synthetic overlays. Contrasting black accents land on the ASICS tongue patch and heel overlay, marked with mismatched GEL Kayano 14 and UNAFFECTED branding on the lateral side of each shoe. The sneaker rides on a lightweight EVA midsole with visible GEL cushioning in the forefoot and heel.

Name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Up There Kookaburra
Description: The Up There x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Kookaburra’ takes inspiration from a laughing bird species native to Australia. The colors of the ‘scruffy larrikin’ are mirrored in the design of the upper, featuring an off-white mesh base with blue leather side stripes on the lateral side. Arrayed across a midfoot leather overlay, brown speckling becomes increasingly dense, transitioning to suede paneling in a solid dark brown finish. Inside the shoe, custom insoles display a kookaburra graphic, along with dual Up There and ASICS branding.

Name: ASICS GT-2160 Above The Clouds
Description: The Above The Clouds x ASICS GT 2160 ‘Shamrock Green’ reunites the creative partners on a lifestyle running shoe that made its original debut in 2011. The mixed-material upper features translucent NEXKIN throughout the vamp and midfoot, along with white open-cell mesh around the collar and heel. Metallic silver side stripes are outlined in green trim, matching the eyelets, interior lining and reinforced toe. Custom insoles display ASICS and Above The Clouds branding. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a sculpted EVA midsole with visible GEL inserts in the heel.

Name: Comme Des Garçons SHIRT x EX89 'White'
Description: The Comme Des Garçons SHIRT x ASICS EX89 ‘White’ presents a collaborative take on a lifestyle model inspired by the GEL-EXTREME, a vintage hoops shoe from 1989. The low-top sports a white leather upper, contrasted by a crimson textile lining and navy side stripes outlined in red trim. Dual branding decorates the woven tongue tag and sockliner. The sneaker sits atop an updated rubber cupsole, featuring vintage off-white sidewalls and an interior foam wedge built with ASICS’ FF BLAST foam.

Name: Comme Des Garçons SHIRT x EX89 'Navy'
Description: The Comme Des Garçons SHIRT x ASICS EX89 ‘Navy’ reunites the partner brands on a lifestyle silhouette inspired by the GEL-EXTREME basketball shoe from 1989. The upper is crafted from navy leather with contrasting white side stripes outlined in red trim. Additional scarlet accents land on the interior lining, molded eyelets, and external heel counter. Dual ASICS and CDG SHIRT branding appears on the woven tongue tag and sockliner. Underfoot, the multicolor rubber outsole features a traction pattern inspired by the view of a city from the sky.

Name: Comme Des Garçons SHIRT x EX89 'Navy'
Description: The Comme Des Garçons SHIRT x ASICS EX89 ‘Navy’ reunites the partner brands on a lifestyle silhouette inspired by the GEL-EXTREME basketball shoe from 1989. The upper is crafted from navy leather with contrasting white side stripes outlined in red trim. Additional scarlet accents land on the interior lining, molded eyelets, and external heel counter. Dual ASICS and CDG SHIRT branding appears on the woven tongue tag and sockliner. Underfoot, the multicolor rubber outsole features a traction pattern inspired by the view of a city from the sky.

Name: Comme Des Garçons SHIRT x EX89 'White'
Description: The Comme Des Garçons SHIRT x ASICS EX89 ‘White’ presents a collaborative take on a lifestyle model inspired by the GEL-EXTREME, a vintage hoops shoe from 1989. The low-top sports a white leather upper, contrasted by a crimson textile lining and navy side stripes outlined in red trim. Dual branding decorates the woven tongue tag and sockliner. The sneaker sits atop an updated rubber cupsole, featuring vintage off-white sidewalls and an interior foam wedge built with ASICS’ FF BLAST foam.

Name: ASICS Gel-NYC Bodega After-Hours
Description: The Bodega x ASICS GEL NYC ‘After-Hours’ showcases a subdued palette inspired by city living after the sun goes down. The lifestyle running shoe features a chain link-inspired mesh upper, fortified with nubuck and suede overlays in Plum Truffle and Mole. Translucent tiger stripes adorn the lateral quarter panel, while Bodega branding in Blazing Coral appears on the lateral heel. Contrasting pops of color arrive via a diamond knit collar lining in Patrician Purple and a suede back tab in Caliste Green. The sneaker sits atop a lightweight EVA midsole with glittery GEL pods in the forefoot and heel.

Name: ASICS Gel-1130 Cream Kale
Description: The ASICS GEL 1130 ‘Cream Kale’ dresses the lifestyle runner in an airy off-white mesh upper with synthetic overlays in a metallic silver finish. Lush green accents land on the signature side stripes and padded textile lining, along with ASICS branding hits on the tongue and sockliner. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a crisp white EVA midsole, fitted with ASICS’ TRUSSTIC system for midfoot stability and a GEL insert in the heel for impact protection.

Name: ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Kale
Description: The ASICS GEL NYC ‘Cream Kale’ features an upper inspired by the GEL-NIMBUS 3 and GEL-MC PLUS V, highlighted by off-white mesh with leather overlays in a gleaming metallic silver finish — a familiar detail that references ASICS running style from the early 2000s. Green trim outlines the signature side stripes, matching the shoe’s eyelets and branding hits. A lightweight EVA midsole, borrowed from the GEL-CUMULUS 16, packs GEL cushioning in the forefoot and heel for a smooth and comfortable ride.

Name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III OG COSTS Cane Vine
Description: The COSTS x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 OG ‘Cane Vine’ reunites the partner brands on an earthy colorway of the lifestyle running shoe. Inspired by lychee vines, the upper features suede paneling in contrasting brown and muted blue hues. Sand-colored hemp textile appears on the quarter panel, overlaid with tonal leather side stripes outlined in brown. Deco stitching enlivens the split tongue and collar, while mismatched COSTS and ASICS branding adorns the heel tab of each shoe. The sneaker rests on a full-length foam midsole with GEL cushioning in the heel.

Name: HAL STUDIOS x Gel 1130 'Glacier'
Description: The HAL STUDIOS x ASICS Gel 1130 'Glacier' delivers the third and final installment of a collaborative series inspired by the natural world. Taking its cues from glacial environments worldwide, the lifestyle runner sports a chalk white open-mesh upper, fortified with leather overlays in ivory and black. Textural variety is provided by off-white hairy suede detailing on the side stripes and toe cap. The sneaker rides on a lightweight EVA midsole with visible Gel cushioning in the heel for improved impact protection.

Name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III '07 Remastered Kith Marvel X-Men Wolverine 1980 Opened Box (Trading Card Not Included)
Description: Commemorating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise, the Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Wolverine 1980’ pays homage to the diminutive mutant superhero with self-healing powers. Inspired by the character’s ‘80s-era suit, the upper combines yellow perforated suede with dark brown leather overlays and red leather side stripes. ‘Wolverine’ branding appears on the insole, while ‘X-Men’ and ‘Fieg’ are embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe. Anchoring the sneaker is a white EVA midsole, featuring Gel cushioning in the heel and a black rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: Kith x Marvel x Gel Lyte 3 '07 Remastered 'X-Men 60th Anniversary - Gambit'
Description: Launching as part of a footwear collection celebrating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise, the Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Gambit’ takes inspiration from the mutant superhero with the power to manipulate kinetic energy. The lifestyle runner makes use of a smooth nubuck upper, featuring a beige base with salmon-colored overlays and crimson leather side stripes. ‘Fieg’ and ‘X-Men’ are embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe, while the sockliner is branded with a custom Gambit label. A full-length EVA midsole, finished in white with ASICS’ Gel technology in the heel, provides lightweight cushioning.

Name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III '07 Remastered Kith Marvel X-Men Gambit Opened Box (Trading Card Not Included)
Description: Launching as part of a footwear collection celebrating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise, the Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Gambit’ takes inspiration from the mutant superhero with the power to manipulate kinetic energy. The lifestyle runner makes use of a smooth nubuck upper, featuring a beige base with salmon-colored overlays and crimson leather side stripes. ‘Fieg’ and ‘X-Men’ are embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe, while the sockliner is branded with a custom Gambit label. A full-length EVA midsole, finished in white with ASICS’ Gel technology in the heel, provides lightweight cushioning.

Name: Kith x Marvel x Gel Lyte 3 '07 Remastered 'X-Men 60th Anniversary - Cyclops'
Description: The Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Cyclops’ represents one of seven special-edition colorways celebrating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise. Inspired by Cyclops’ laser eyes and suit, the lifestyle runner features a blue mesh upper with navy suede overlays, yellow leather side stripes and crimson eyelets. In addition to a ‘Cyclops’ label on the insole, unique branding hits include ‘X-Men’ and ‘Fieg’ embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe. The sneaker rests on a crisp white EVA midsole with Gel cushioning in the heel.

Name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III '07 Remastered Kith Marvel X-Men Cyclops Opened Box (Trading Card Not Included)
Description: The Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Cyclops’ represents one of seven special-edition colorways celebrating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise. Inspired by Cyclops’ laser eyes and suit, the lifestyle runner features a blue mesh upper with navy suede overlays, yellow leather side stripes and crimson eyelets. In addition to a ‘Cyclops’ label on the insole, unique branding hits include ‘X-Men’ and ‘Fieg’ embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe. The sneaker rests on a crisp white EVA midsole with Gel cushioning in the heel.

Name: Kith x Marvel x Gel Lyte 3 '07 Remastered 'X-Men 60th Anniversary - Rogue'
Description: Dropping as part of a seven-piece collection celebrating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise, the Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Rogue’ honors the mutant superhero with the power to absorb a person’s life force through physical contact. The character’s original suit is mirrored in the design of the upper, featuring a dark green suede base with contrasting yellow leather overlays and olive leather side stripes. ‘Fieg’ and ‘X-Men’ are embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe, while custom ‘Rogue’ labels decorate the sockliners. The retro runner rides on an EVA midsole, fitted with Gel cushioning in the heel and supported underfoot by a black rubber outsole.

Name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III '07 Remastered Kith Marvel X-Men Storm Opened Box (Trading Card Not Included)
Description: The Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Storm’ is drawn from a sneaker pack celebrating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise. Reflecting Storm’s silvery hair and dark suit, the lifestyle runner features a faux pony hair upper with a white base, grey overlays and black leather side stripes. A custom ‘Storm’ label adorns the sockliner, while mismatched ‘Fieg’ and ‘X-men’ branding is embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a full-length EVA midsole with ASICS’ Gel technology in the heel.

Name: Kith x Marvel x Gel Lyte 3 '07 Remastered 'X-Men 60th Anniversary - Wolverine 1980'
Description: Commemorating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise, the Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Wolverine 1980’ pays homage to the diminutive mutant superhero with self-healing powers. Inspired by the character’s ‘80s-era suit, the upper combines yellow perforated suede with dark brown leather overlays and red leather side stripes. ‘Wolverine’ branding appears on the insole, while ‘X-Men’ and ‘Fieg’ are embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe. Anchoring the sneaker is a white EVA midsole, featuring Gel cushioning in the heel and a black rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III '07 Remastered Kith Marvel X-Men Wolverine 1975 Opened Box (Trading Card Not Included)
Description: The Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Wolverine 1975’ is taken from a collaborative footwear collection recognizing the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise. The most limited colorway in the seven-piece pack, this pair is inspired by Wolverine’s original suit and features a yellow perforated suede upper with black leather overlays and blue leather side stripes. In addition to ‘Wolverine’ insoles, unique branding elements include ‘X-Men’ and ‘Fieg’ embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe. The lifestyle runner sits atop a white EVA midsole with Gel cushioning in the heel.

Name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III '07 Remastered Kith Marvel X-Men Beast Opened Box (Trading Card Not Included)
Description: The Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Beast’ is taken from a capsule collection celebrating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise. This pair pays homage to the original X-Men character known as Beast, whose signature blue fur is reflected in the hairy pigskin suede upper. Contrasting white accents land on the leather side stripes, molded TPU eyelets, and textile collar lining. In addition to ‘Beast’ sockliners, unique branding elements include ‘X-Men’ and ‘Fieg’ embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe. The lifestyle runner sits atop a white EVA midsole, supported underfoot by a durable black rubber outsole.

Name: Kith x Marvel x Gel Lyte 3 '07 Remastered 'X-Men 60th Anniversary - Beast'
Description: The Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Beast’ is taken from a capsule collection celebrating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise. The lifestyle runner sits atop a white EVA midsole, supported underfoot by a durable black rubber outsole.

Name: Kith x Marvel x Gel Lyte 3 '07 Remastered 'X-Men 60th Anniversary - Wolverine 1975'

The most limited colorway in the seven-piece pack, this pair is inspired by Wolverine’s original suit and features a yellow perforated suede upper with black leather overlays and blue leather side stripes. In addition to ‘Wolverine’ insoles, unique branding elements include ‘X-Men’ and ‘Fieg’ embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe. The lifestyle runner sits atop a white EVA midsole with Gel cushioning in the heel.

Name: Kith x Marvel x Gel Lyte 3 '07 Remastered 'X-Men 60th Anniversary - Storm'
Description: The Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Storm’ is drawn from a sneaker pack celebrating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise. Reflecting Storm’s silvery hair and dark suit, the lifestyle runner features a faux pony hair upper with a white base, grey overlays and black leather side stripes. A custom ‘Storm’ label adorns the sockliner, while mismatched ‘Fieg’ and ‘X-men’ branding is embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a full-length EVA midsole with ASICS’ Gel technology in the heel.

Name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III '07 Remastered Kith Marvel X-Men Rogue Opened Box (Trading Card Not Included)
Description: Dropping as part of a seven-piece collection celebrating the 60th anniversary of Marvel Comics’ X-Men franchise, the Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 3 ‘Rogue’ honors the mutant superhero with the power to absorb a person’s life force through physical contact. The character’s original suit is mirrored in the design of the upper, featuring a dark green suede base with contrasting yellow leather overlays and olive leather side stripes. ‘Fieg’ and ‘X-Men’ are embroidered on the split tongue of each shoe, while custom ‘Rogue’ labels decorate the sockliners. The retro runner rides on an EVA midsole, fitted with Gel cushioning in the heel and supported underfoot by a black rubber outsole.

Name: ASICS GT-2160 DIME Arctic Wolf
Description: The Dime x ASICS GT 2160 ‘Arctic Wolf’ presents the Montreal skate brand’s minimalist interpretation of the retro-inspired lifestyle runner. Finished in a color-fade effect in white and grey, the mesh upper features welded off-white side stripes and a shiny heel overlay in metallic silver. Mismatched ASICS and Dime logos adorn each tongue, while the latter brand gets an additional callout on the lateral heel. Visible Gel cushioning enhances the full-length EVA midsole, accented with a gradient streak of cream, tan and grey.

Name: ASICS GT-2160 Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Black
Description: The Cecilie Bahnsen x ASICS GT 2160 ‘Black’ brings the Danish designer’s feminine artistry to the lifestyle running shoe. A monochromatic black finish is applied to the upper, crafted from translucent ripstop with floral lines and glossy patent leather overlays. Inspired by a Mary Jane shoe, the reworked build replaces a traditional tongue with a cut-out panel secured with a floral strap and decorative laces. A matching black foam midsole packs visible Gel cushioning in the heel for a comfortable ride.

Name: ASICS Gel-Lyte V Concepts Libertea
Description: The Concepts x ASICS Gel Lyte 5 ‘Libertea’ showcases a patriotic palette celebrating the 30th anniversary of the lifestyle running shoe. Inspired by Concepts’ ‘Boston Tea Party’ Gel Lyte 3 from 2015, the color-blocked suede upper combines an off-white forefoot with a crimson heel, alongside contrasting navy accents on the tongue, collar and eyestay. The right side of each shoe pairs metallic gold side stripes with a red mesh backdrop, while the opposite side features metallic silver side stripes and navy mesh paneling. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a white EVA midsole, enlivened with a splash of scarlet along the heel.

Name: ASICS GT-2160 Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Metallic Silver (Women's)
Description: The Cecilie Bahnsen x ASICS GT 2160 ‘Pure Silver’ delivers the Danish designer’s couture-inspired take on the lifestyle running shoe. Reimagined as a Mary Jane hybrid, the slip-on features a transparent upper with illustrated floral lines and shiny metallic silver overlays. The tongue is removed, revealing a cut-out panel secured with decorative laces and a Velcro strap with floral embellishments. The sneaker rests on a sculpted foam midsole with ASICS Gel cushioning in the heel.

Name: ASICS Gel-1130 Kith Cream Starlight Blue
Description: The Kith x ASICS Gel 1130 ‘Cream Starlight Blue’ is taken from a collaborative four-piece footwear collection. The lifestyle runner carries an airy white mesh upper with durable synthetic leather overlays in a metallic silver finish. Side stripes in bright teal provide pastel pops of color. The lightweight build rests on a high-rebound SpEVA midsole, fitted with visible ASICS Gel cushioning in the heel. Underfoot, a durable black rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

Name: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Kith Cream Scarab
Description: Dropping as part of a collaborative four-piece pack, the Kith x ASICS Gel Kayano 14 ‘Cream Scarab’ brings a refined palette to the lifestyle runner. Showcasing a late 2000s aesthetic, the upper blends airy off-white mesh with shiny synthetic leather overlays in metallic silver. Contrasting hits of color arrive via signature side stripes in a dark green hue. A vintage finish is applied to the lightweight EVA midsole, featuring visible Gel cushioning in the heel for a comfortable ride.

Name: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Kith Cream Antler
Description: Launching as part of a four-piece footwear collection, the Kith x ASICS Gel Kayano 14 ‘Cream Antler’ delivers a subtle colorway of the retro running shoe. Ventilated off-white mesh is utilized on the upper, contrasted by metallic silver synthetic leather overlays and signature side stripes in a dull mauve hue. ASICS branding appears on the tongue, while ‘Gel Kayano 14’ is inscribed on the lateral heel. The sneaker rides on a full-length EVA midsole with visible Gel cushioning in the heel.

Name: ASICS Gel-1130 Kith Cream Scarab
Description: Drawn from a four-piece footwear collection, the Kith x ASICS Gel 1130 ‘Cream Scarab’ showcases a lightweight, summer-ready build with high-rebound cushioning. The lifestyle running shoe makes use of a breathable off-white mesh upper, contrasted by dark green side stripes and synthetic leather overlays in metallic silver. Underpinning the sneaker is a responsive SpEVA midsole, fitted with visible Gel cushioning in the heel and ASICS’ TRUSSTIC support system under the midfoot.

Name: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Black Metallic Plum
Description: The ASICS Gel Kayano 14 ‘Silver Cream’ features a distinctive color scheme and build that distills a 2000s running-shoe aesthetic. Polished black side stripes decorate an off-white mesh upper, fortified with durable synthetic overlays in a gleaming metallic silver finish. The lifestyle runner rides on a lightweight EVA midsole with visible Gel cushioning in the forefoot and heel. Underfoot, the rubber outsole is fitted with ASICS Trusstic System, good for midfoot support and stability.

Name: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 JJJJound Silver White
Description: The JJJJound x ASICS Gel Kayano 14 ‘Silver White’ introduces the partner brands’ debut collaboration. Reflecting the distinctive running-shoe aesthetic of the late 2000s, the upper combines breathable white mesh with metallic silver overlays and reflective accents. Mismatched branding decorates the lateral heel of the left and right shoe, featuring a ‘JJJJound’ wordmark on the latter and ‘Gel Kayano 14’ on the former. A cream-colored EVA midsole packs visible Gel cushioning in the forefoot and heel for a smooth ride.

Name: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Hi Made With Love (GS)
Description: Dropping as part of the brand’s Valentine’s Day collection, the Converse Chuck Taylor All Star High GS ‘White’ carries a traditional canvas upper festooned with unique details in honor of February 14. They include heart-printed laces, an embroidered heart on the lateral side and a ‘Made With Love’ graphic on the opposite side. Underfoot, the white rubber outsole features a traditional diamond traction pattern and an all-over print made up of additional red hearts.

Name: Converse Skidgrip Ox Oil Green
Description: The Converse Skid Grip Low ‘Malachite Green’ updates an archival model that debuted back in 1910 as the Converse Circular Vamp Oxford (CVO). It would adopt its current name in the 1960s, a reference to the added no-slip rubber sole originally made for boating. The military-inspired build features varying shades of teal on the upper, composed of jungle cloth on the lateral side and suede on the opposite side. Green waxed canvas is utilized on the tongue and vamp.

Name: Converse Run Star Hike Ox Black White Gum
Description: The Converse Run Star Hike Low ‘Black Gum’ features the traditional canvas upper of the iconic Chuck Taylor All Star, complete with chrome eyelets, contrast stitching and a durable white rubber toe cap. The sneaker’s tooling is radically overhauled with a platform midsole and two-piece color-blocked outsole. Black rubber wraps up the heel, while gum rubber extends up the toe, both configured in a sawtooth pattern for optimal grip.

Name: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star Hi Scooby-Doo Good Guys Bad Guys (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the Scooby-Doo x Converse Chuck Taylor All Star High GS ‘The Gang and Villains’ is drawn from a larger collection celebrating the long-running animated franchise. The white canvas upper features a graphic print on the lateral side that depicts Scooby and Shaggy in a frightened emotional state. A black woven tongue tag is inscribed with ‘Scooby-Doo!’ on the exterior side and ‘Ruh-Roh!’ on the interior.

Name: Yeezy 700 V3 'Azael' 2023
Description: The 2023 edition of the adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Azael’ brings back a colorway originally released in 2019. The futuristic runner features an upper crafted from monofilament engineered mesh in subdued white and grey tones. A glow-in-the-dark RPU cage offers added structure and durability, while an interior bootie delivers a snug, comfortable fit. A PU encapsulated EVA midsole provides lightweight cushioning with every step. Underfoot, a blue-tinted rubber outsole utilizes a herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip.

Name: adidas Yeezy Slide Granite
Description: The adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Granite’ accentuates the sandal’s sleek, modern lines with a tonal dark grey finish. Built with a solitary piece of lightweight and durable EVA foam, the slip-on delivers a comfortable fit, thanks to the combination of a wide strap upper and soft footbed. The latter is embellished with adidas’ three-stripe logo, representing the only bit of exterior branding. The outsole features strategic groove placement for improved traction and a smooth, natural ride.

Name: Yeezy Boost 700 'Utility Black' 2023
Description: The 2023 reissue of the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Utility Black’ brings back a stealthy colorway originally released in 2019. The retro-inspired model carries a ventilated black mesh upper with tonal overlays in leather and suede. Reflective accents, including hidden three-stripes beneath the mesh quarter panel, offer improved visibility in low-light conditions. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a drop-in Boost midsole, housed within a sculpted PU carrier for added durability. Underfoot, a gum rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for superior grip.

Name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Dark Salt
Description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘MX Dark Salt’ presents a nuanced colorway that merges a full spectrum of neutral tones. Secured with standard lace closure, the Primeknit upper is dressed in complementary shades of silver, grey and black. The swirling design is offset by a side stripe in black, which cuts through the lateral side and matches the webbing pull tab affixed to the heel. Responsive cushioning is provided by a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a ribbed TPU cage and supported by a grippy rubber outsole.

Name: adidas Stan Smith The Simpsons Homer Simpson
Description: The Simpsons x adidas Stan Smith ‘Homer Simpson’ pays tribute to the iconic animated TV dad. The character’s name is stamped in gold-foil lettering on the white leather upper, while his likeness appears on the printed Stan Smith tag that adorns the tongue. The shoe’s standout feature takes the form of the heel tab, which depicts a snapshot of an instantly recognizable GIF — that of a wide-eyed Homer Simpson walking backward into lush green hedges. Underpinning the sneaker is a durable rubber cupsole in an antique cream-colored finish.

Name: adidas Yeezy Slide Slate Grey
Description: The adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Slate Grey’ presents a neutral colorway of the lightweight and durable slip-on silhouette. A medium grey finish is applied to the one-piece build, composed of injected EVA foam with a seamless wide-strap upper. Exterior branding is limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo debossed on the footbed, featuring a soft top layer for step-in comfort. Underfoot, deep grooves in the outsole provide superior traction and a comfortable ride.

Name: Yeezy Boost 700 'Wave Runner' 2023
Description: The 2023 edition of the Yeezy Boost 700 brings back the original 'Wave Runner' colorway, first released in 2017. The upper utilizes mixed materials, including leather, mesh, suede and 3M, while the sculpted midsole houses Boost for lightweight cushioning. The shoe is mostly grey and black, save for a splash of blue and teal on the forefoot, two orange hits on the midsole and yellow laces.

Name: adidas Yeezy Slide Slate Marine
Description: The adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Slate Marine’ pairs a minimalist design with a tonal finish in a subdued shade of blue. Built with a single piece of injected EVA foam, the slip-on boasts a wide strap upper that entirely covers the top of the foot. Exterior branding is limited to adidas’ three stripes logo, debossed on the soft top lay of the footbed. Underfoot, the outsole features a series of horizontal grooves for improved cushioning and traction.

Name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Carbon
Description: The adidas Yeezy Foam Runner ‘Carbon’ brings a stealthy one-note finish to the futuristic slip-on. A dark shade of grey is applied to the one-piece build, made with injected EVA foam and featuring flowing lines and a sculpted heel designed to cradle the back of the foot. Strategically mapped vents throughout the vamp and side panels provide enhanced breathability, while the textured footbed offers a comfortable fit. Underpinning the clog-like silhouette is a durable rubber outsole.

Name: adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Onyx
Description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 CMPCT ‘Slate Onyx’ presents a neutral colorway of the lifestyle silhouette. Black and grey threads are woven into the upper, featuring an engineered 3D knit build that hugs the foot in lightweight support. Along with a stretchy sock-like collar, no-tie elastic laces provide easy on and off. The sneaker rides on a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a semi-translucent TPU cage and reinforced by a durable rubber outsole.

Name: Bad Bunny x Campus 'Chalky Brown'
Description: Continuing a creative partnership that began in 2021, the Bad Bunny x adidas Campus ‘Chalky Brown’ delivers the chart-topping recording artist’s distinctive take on the iconic silhouette. The low-top makes use of a brown hairy suede upper, accented with tonal three-stripe branding and equipped with double-tongue construction. Inspired by ocean waves, an evolved rubber mudguard in a cream-colored finish gives way to a durable rubber cupsole, featuring a herringbone traction pattern underfoot.

Name: adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Triple Black
Description: The Bad Bunny x adidas Response CL ‘Triple Black’ reunites the creative partners on a stealthy colorway of the lifestyle runner. The upper is composed of breathable black mesh, accented with navy TPU three-stripes and bolstered with tonal wavy overlays in durable synthetic leather. Tonal adidas branding appears on the tongue, while Bad Bunny’s third eye graphic decorates the heel tab. The sneaker rides on a full-length EVA midsole in a matching black finish.

Name: adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Panda
Description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 CMPCT ‘Panda’ showcases neutral tones on a casual sneaker that marries sock-like comfort with responsive cushioning. Rendered in white and grey, the 3D knitted upper is equipped with elastic no-tie laces for easy on and off. A stretchy collar in black extends up the ankle for a secure, locked-in fit. The lightweight build is mounted on a springy Boost midsole, enveloped in a semi-translucent TPU cage for improved durability and support.

Name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon Beluga
Description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Carbon Beluga’ brings together vivid pops of color with a patterned design. Rope laces secure the breathable Primeknit upper, rendered in a dark grey finish with wavy black lines and contrasting orange speckles. On the lateral side, a matching orange stripe displays ‘SPLY-350’ branding. Responsive cushioning is provided by a full-length Boost midsole, housed within a ribbed TPU cage and supported underfoot by a durable rubber outsole.

Name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR MX Cinder
Description: The adidas Yeezy Foam Runner ‘MX Cinder’ enlivens the slip-on silhouette with cooling splashes of color. Built with injected EVA foam, the one-piece upper is rendered in an earthy mix of brown and tan shades. Atop the vamp, a solid black finish is contrasted by unexpected bursts of aqua blue. A series of strategically mapped vents provide enhanced breathability, while the soft top layer of the footbed delivers step-in comfort. Underfoot, the contoured outsole features a wavy tread for optimal grip.

Name: adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Teal
Description: The adidas Yeezy 450 ‘Stone Teal’ delivers a stealthy colorway of the lifestyle silhouette. A neutral grey finish is applied to the one-piece knit upper, secured with traditional lace closure and a stretchy sock-like collar. A hint of teal along the back heel adds a subtle pop of color, disrupting the shoe’s monochrome palette. The lightweight build is mounted on a PU-injected midsole, featuring distinctive lines that give the sneaker its unique, one-of-a-kind aesthetic.

Name: BAPE x Forum Low 84 '30th Anniversary - Blue'
Description: Celebrating the influential streetwear brand’s 30th anniversary, the BAPE x adidas Forum Low 84 ‘’Blue’ updates the heritage hoops shoe with a street-ready aesthetic. BAPE’s ABC Camo print in varying shades of blue is applied to the leather upper, contrasted by white paneling on the toe box and midfoot. The latter is accented with navy three-stripes, while metallic silver 30th anniversary branding decorates the tongue tag and lace dubrae. Anchoring the sneaker is a durable cupsole, highlighted by aged sidewalls and a navy rubber outsole.

Name: Gucci Ace Panther
Description: The ‘Panther’ edition of Gucci’s classic low-top Ace sneaker is adorned with an iconic embroidered black panther appliqué. The premium white leather upper features green snake detailing at the heel and a full-length textured rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 14 Retro Black White
Description: The Air Jordan 14 Retro ‘Black White’ arrives in an essential two-tone colorway. Crafted from black suede, the upper features an asymmetrical collar and stitched lines throughout the side panel. On the lateral side, a Jumpman badge takes inspiration from Ferrari’s prancing horse emblem. White accents stand out on the black Phylon midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot and heel. A herringbone-pattern rubber outsole delivers grippy traction underfoot.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Fear Pack (2023)
Description: The 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Fear’ brings back a 2013 AJ3 colorway that was originally released alongside an Air Jordan 4 and 5. A dark grey nubuck upper is complemented with tonal elephant print overlays at the forefoot and heel. Black suede is utilized on the collar and tongue, featuring a stitched Jumpman logo in Total Orange. The vibrant color is repeated on the shoe’s eyelets, along with a second Jumpman icon on the back heel. An orange-tinged Air-sole unit adds lightweight cushioning to a tri-tone polyurethane midsole.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Fear Pack (2023) (GS)
Description: Offered in grade school sizing, the 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 3 Retro GS ‘Fear’ revives a sleek colorway originally released in 2013. The upper is crafted from dark grey nubuck with tonal elephant print overlays at the forefoot and heel. Total Orange accents land on the shoe’s eyelets, along with Jumpman branding hits at the tongue and molded heel tab. The mid-top rides on an Air-assisted foam midsole, featuring a crisp white finish with a contrasting topline in a gradient blend of grey and black.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro A Ma Maniére Dusk
Description: The A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Dusk’ reunites the creative partners on a two sneaker collaborative pack. This pair carries a black nubuck upper, updated with a slimmed-down collar and pre-yellowed quarter panel netting formed with an interlocking series of A Ma Maniére’s signature ‘A’ logo. ‘Nike Air’ branding is embroidered on the back heel in tonal fashion, while silver reflective tongues display mismatched Jumpman and A Ma Maniére branding. The sneaker sits atop a matching black polyurethane midsole with shark-tooth detailing in a dark burgundy hue. A pre-aged translucent rubber outsole featuring the Atlanta-based retailer’s logo provides durable traction underfoot.

Name: Jordan 13 Retro Wheat (2023) (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS ‘Wheat’ brings back a two-tone colorway originally released in 2004. The upper features white leather construction on the shoe’s dimpled overlays and toe, along with beige suede paneling that extends from the midfoot and around the heel. A green-tinted holograph ‘eye’ adorns the lateral collar, while an embroidered Jumpman graces the tongue. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a white Phylon midsole, partially wrapped in beige synthetic suede and supported by a panther-paw rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Medium Olive (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro SE GS Craft in ‘Olive’ features a layered upper in nubuck and suede. Quarter panels are updated with embossed suede in a gridded pattern, replacing the TPU netting of the original. Contrasting black accents settle on the shoe’s leather support wings, molded eyelets and textile collar lining. A cream-colored Jumpman logo adorns the woven tongue tag and semi-translucent back tab. Undergirding the sneaker is a lightweight foam midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Medium Olive (PS)
Description: Built for little kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro SE GS Craft in ‘Olive’ makes use of a layered upper in a tonal blend of nubuck and suede. The quarter panel discards the TPU netting of the original in favor of embossed suede in a gridded pattern. Black textile lines the collar, matching the eyelets and leather support wings. A cream-hued Jumpman logo adorns the tongue and semi-translucent back tab. The mid-top rests on a white foam midsole, supported by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro A Ma Maniére Dawn (Women's)
Description: Launching as part of a two-piece collaborative pack, the A Ma Maniére x Women’s Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Dawn’ sports a pale grey leather upper, revised with a slimmed-down collar and pre-yellowed quarter panel netting formed with A Ma Maniére’s ‘A’ logo. Additional branding elements include an embroidered ‘23’ on the lateral heel, Nike Air branding on the back heel, and mismatched Jumpman and ‘A’ logos on each silver reflective tongue. Blue shark tooth detailing enlivens a black polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel. A pre-aged translucent rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro Origins
Description: The Air Jordan 2 Retro ‘Origins’ showcases a distinctive color scheme that nods to the shoe’s premium roots. (The original 1986 release paired an elegant Swooshless design with made-in-Italy construction.) This pair dons a white leather upper with faux lizard skin on the midfoot overlay. The latter is outlined in two-tone piping in red and green, with the contrasting hues making a repeat appearance on the Nike-branded heel tab. Crimson textile lines the high-cut collar, matching the embossed Wings logo that decorates the tongue. A vintage off-white finish is applied to the polyurethane midsole, fitted with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and supported by a two-tone rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro Origins (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 2 Retro GS ‘Origins’ gets dressed in a color scheme that references the silhouette’s continental provenance. (The original 1986 launch paired premium materials with made-in-Italy craftsmanship.) Built with smooth white leather, the upper retains the lizard-textured overlay of the OG AJ2. The midfoot panel is surrounded by red and green piping, with the contrasting hues making repeat appearances on the shoe’s heel and interior lining. Branding elements include a Nike wordmark on the back tab and an embossed Wings logo on the tongue. Anchoring the sneaker is an off-white foam midsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro Origins (PS)
Description: Made for little kids, the Air Jordan 2 Retro PS ‘Origins’ features accent colors inspired by the shoe’s premium ‘80s roots. The legacy silhouette makes use of a white leather upper with a lizard-textured midfoot overlay outlined in red and green piping. Exterior branding elements are limited to an embossed Wings logo on the tongue and a Nike wordmark on the heel tab, both of which are rendered in a bold Fire Red finish. A contrasting hit of Fir Green lands on the heel counter. Anchoring the sneaker is a vintage off-white midsole built with cushy foam.

Name: Jordan 11 Retro DMP Gratitude (2023) (GS)
Description: Crafted for big kids, he Air Jordan 11 Retro GS ‘Gratitude / Defining Moments’ features color blocking reminiscent of the iconic ‘Concord’ AJ11, highlighted by a white leather upper with tonal webbing eyelets and a contrasting black mudguard in glossy patent leather. A metallic gold Jumpman shines on the lateral collar, matching the stylized ‘23’ stamped on the back tab. The sneaker rests on a cushy white Phylon midsole, supported underfoot by a cream-tinted semi-translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 11 Retro DMP Gratitude (2023)
Description: The 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Gratitude / Defining Moments', also known as 'DMP', brings back a coveted colorway of the legacy model, originally paired with an Air Jordan 6 as one-half of the 'Defining Moments Pack' from 2006. Inspired by the OG 'Concord' colorway, the championship silhouette features a white tumbled leather upper with tonal webbing eyelets and a black patent leather mudguard. Metallic gold accents land on the shoe's branding elements, including an embossed Jumpman logo on the lateral ankle and a '23' stamped on the heel tab. The sneaker rides on a Phylon midsole, supported by a carbon fiber shank plate and a translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro Georgetown
Description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro SE ‘Midnight Navy’ highlights a tonal finish on the textile and suede upper, equipped with a padded collar and breathable quarter panel netting. Molded black eyelets match the Jumpman logos that decorate the tongue and back heel. The sneaker sits atop a white polyurethane midsole with speckled shark-tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. A blue-tinted translucent rubber outsole featuring herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip completes the look.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro Georgetown (GS)
Description: Built for big kids, the Air Jordan 5 Retro SE GS ‘Midnight Navy’ utilizes textile paneling on the midfoot and toe box, while tonal suede construction appears throughout the padded collar and heel overlay. The latter is accented with an embroidered black Jumpman, matching a second Jumpman logo on the tongue. A contrasting white foam midsole features speckled shark tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole yields durable traction.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Royal Reimagined
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Royal Reimagined’ brings back the original 1985 colorway utilizing different materials. Replacing the leather construction of the original, the upper is draped in smooth suede, featuring a black base with contrasting royal blue accents on the toe box, Swoosh, heel and collar overlay. The latter is marked with the iconic Jordan Wings logo, while a woven Nike Air tag adorns the breathable nylon tongue. The classic silhouette is mounted on a sturdy rubber cupsole, highlighted by white sidewalls and a grippy royal blue outsole.

Name: Jordan 12 Retro Cherry (2023)
Description: The 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Cherry’ reintroduces the OG colorway of the shoe that Michael Jordan wore during his penultimate championship season. Highlighted with radiating stitched lines, the white leather upper is fortified with lizard-textured overlays in a bold scarlet finish. The Jumpman logo graces the tongue in black embroidery, matching the shoe’s textile collar lining. The sneaker rides on a Phylon midsole with full-length Zoom Air cushioning. Underfoot, the semi-translucent red rubber outsole reveals black herringbone traction pods and an exposed carbon fiber shank plate.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Chris Paul
Description: The Chris Paul x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘Give Them Flowers’ features a debossed tonal floral pattern on the white leather upper, accented with a signature Swoosh in off-white hairy suede. The latter material reappears on the toe box and back tab, marked with the Wings logo for an OG touch. Atop the suede tongue, a woven Nike Air tag displays the phrase ‘Give Them Flowers’ on the interior side. A multicolor floral print adds vibrant pops of color to the insole and translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT 2 Día De Muertos
Description: Launching as part of Nike’s annual Day of the Dead celebration, the Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort 2 ‘Día De Muertos’ features a faux distressed finish throughout the leather upper. A brush-off effect in black and ivory is accompanied by a floral design atop the toe box and quarter panel. On the lateral heel, a skull graphic in gold embroidery delivers a contrasting pop of color. The updated rubber cupsole houses a Zoom Air heel unit encapsulated in an interior wedge made with Jordan Formula 23 foam.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Satin Bred (Women's)
Description: The Women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Satin Bred’ 2023 mirrors an extremely limited AJ1 release from 2016. Finished in the iconic bred color scheme, the high-top dons an upper built entirely with shiny satin. OG-inspired branding elements feature a woven Nike tag atop the tongue and a stitched Jordan Wings logo on the lateral collar flap. The sneaker rests on a contrasting white midsole, featuring an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel and a crimson rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro SP J Balvin Medellín Sunset
Description: The J Balvin x Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Medellín Sunset' reunites the creative partners on a tropical colorway of the iconic silhouette. Inspired by the breathtaking sunsets of J Balvin’s hometown of Medellin, Colombia, this special-edition AJ3 sports an ivory-colored leather upper with tonal elephant print overlays at the forefoot and heel. A gradient blend of yellow, orange and dark purple lands on the rear midsole and molded back tab, featuring mismatched Nike branding on the left shoe and J Balvin’s smiley face icon on the right. An embroidered gold Jumpman graces the tongue. Undergirding the sneaker is a blue-tinged translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Red Cement (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS ‘Red Cement’ combines OG color blocking with a familiar Chicago-inspired palette. The mid-top carries a white leather upper, featuring breathable quarter panel netting and molded eyelets in black. The shoe’s signature support wings are finished in crimson with black speckled detailing, matching the Jumpman-branded heel tag. A second Jumpman appears on the Flight tongue tag. The mid-top is mounted on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, fitted with exposed Air-sole cushioning and supported by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Red Cement
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Red Cement’ showcases color blocking that recalls the OG ‘White Cement’ colorway. The mid-top carries a white leather upper with tonal quarter panel netting and contrasting black accents on the molded eyelets and interior lining. Vibrant hits of Fire Red — accompanied by black speckled detailing — land on the shoe’s support wings, polyurethane midsole and heel tab. The latter features embossed Jumpman branding. A second Jumpman icon decorates the Flight tongue tag. Underfoot, a herringbone-traction rubber outsole delivers superior grip.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Palomino
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Palomino’ merges a luxe build with OG-inspired two-tone color blocking. The sneaker icon carries a black leather upper, accented with aged brown nubuck on the toe box, Swoosh, heel overlay and collar flap. The latter is marked with a black Wings logo on the lateral side, while the woven tongue tag displays a Nike logo with metallic gold lettering. A contrasting off-white finish is applied to the midsole, built with stitched sidewall construction and encapsulated Air-sole cushioning. Underfoot, a brown rubber outsole features a traction pattern designed to grip the hardwood.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro Burgundy (2023)
Description: The 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 5 Retro SE ‘Burgundy’ brings back a 2006 colorway from Jordan Brand’s Lifestyle Series. The legacy silhouette utilizes a burgundy suede upper, accented with contrast stitching and breathable translucent netting on the quarter panel. Embroidered Jumpman branding decorates the heel overlay and tongue, treated with a sliver reflective finish for added visibility during low-light conditions. A color-matched polyurethane features speckled shark-tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit nestled in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent herringbone-traction outsole delivers reliable grip.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Frozen Moments (Women's)
Description: The Women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Frozen Moments’ features a pale grey suede upper with a color-matched forefoot overlay in glossy leather. Breathable netting is utilized on the throat and quarter panel, while the shoe’s molded eyelets and support wings shine in a metallic silver finish. Tonal Jumpman branding embellishes the tongue and molded heel tab. Anchoring the sneaker is a grey foam midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Union LA Bephies Beauty Supply Summer of ‘96
Description: The Union LA x Bephie’s Beauty Supply x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP 'Summer of '96' delivers a three-way collaboration that reunites Jordan Brand with Chris Gibbs and Beth Birkett Gibbs. Their unique take on the iconic silhouette features a white leather upper with exposed green stitching, a pale grey Swoosh and woven detailing that recalls the Nike Air Footscape Woven. Yellow trim outlines the shoe’s classic lines, matching the laces and the discreet ‘UN/LA’ label that adorns the lateral ankle. Additional branding elements include a woven Nike Air tongue tag and a tonal Wings logo stamped on the collar flap. A vintage pre-yellowed finish is applied to the durable rubber cupsole.

Name: Jordan 13 Retro Wolf Grey (2023) (TD)
Description: Built for a new generation of Michael Jordan fans, the Air Jordan 13 Retro TD ‘White Wolf Grey’ delivers a neutral colorway in celebration of the classic silhouette’s 25th anniversary. Dimpled overlays in white tumbled leather dominate the upper, featuring grey suede paneling and a forefoot built with white tumbled leather. An embroidered Jumpman in True Red adorns the tongue, while the 13’s signature holographic eye is embedded in the lateral collar. Underfoot, the outsole leverages herringbone traction pods for reliable grip.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Black Toe (2023) (GS)
Description: Scaled down for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG GS ‘Black Toe’ brings back an original 1985 colorway. The low-top carries an all-leather upper that combines a white base with contrasting black accents on the forefoot overlay, eyestay and signature Swoosh. Bold hits of Varsity Red settle on the heel and back tab, the latter marked with a stitched Wings logo. Nike Air branding decorates the tongue tag and sockliner. Encapsulated Air-sole cushioning enhances the midsole, rendered in a classic white finish and supported by a durable crimson rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro Low Dongdan
Description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro Low ‘Dongdan’ pays homage to the legendary streetball courts of Beijing. The low-top sports a black nubuck upper with contrast pink stitching and translucent netting on the quarter panel. A Jumpman icon adorns the silver reflective tongue, while the Dongdan tournament’s logo is embroidered on the back heel. The sneaker rests on a black polyurethane midsole, fitted with visible Air-cushioning and accented with pink shark-tooth detailing covered in black speckles. A pink-tinted translucent rubber outsole delivers grippy traction underfoot.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG UNC Toe (PS)
Description: Inspired by Michael Jordan’s alma mater, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS ‘UNC Toe’ delivers a scaled-down model built for little kids. The high-top makes use of an all-leather upper, featuring a white quarter panel with contrasting black hits on the forefoot overlay, high-cut collar and signature Swoosh. University Blue accents make their way to the toe box, ankle and heel. The sneaker is mounted on a sturdy rubber cupsole that pairs white sidewalls with a Tar Heel blue rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG UNC Toe
Description: Inspired by Michael Jordan’s alma mater, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘UNC Toe’ brings back the distinctive color blocking originally featured on the ‘Bred Toe’ AJ1 from 2018. The high-top utilizes an all-leather upper with white quarter panels and contrasting hits of black on the signature Swoosh and forefoot overlay. University Blue accents make their way to the toe box, heel and collar flap, marked with a retro Wings logo on the lateral side. A woven Nike tag atop the breathable nylon tongue delivers an OG-inspired touch. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a white rubber midsole with an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in a polyurethane wedge. Underfoot, a blue rubber outsole provides durable traction with every step.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG UNC Toe (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS ‘UNC Toe’ showcases a color combination that nods to Michael Jordan’s alma mater. Smooth leather is deployed on the upper, featuring a neutral white and black base with University Blue accents on the toe box, heel overlay and ankle. The shoe’s OG-inspired aesthetic is completed with a woven Nike tongue tag and an embossed Wings logo on the lateral collar flap. Underpinning the sneaker is a white rubber midsole, fitted with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and supported by a grippy rubber outsole in Tar Heel blue.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse
Description: The Marvel x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Next Chapter' delivers a collaborative colorway tied to the animated film 'Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse.’ A play on the original ‘Chicago’ colorway, this reimagined take on the sneaker icon features a white leather upper with black patent leather on the collar and Swoosh. Scarlet overlays are composed of a patchwork mix of different textures and prints — a pieced-together design that nods to the multidimensional Spiderman universe. A retro Wings logo is stamped on the lateral collar flap, while a woven Nike tag decorates the nylon tongue. The high-top rides on a rubber cupsole that pairs aged sidewalls with a crimson semi-translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro SE Craft Light Orewood Brown
Description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro SE ‘Craft’ updates the legacy silhouette with a subtle color palette and a refreshed build. Crafted from taupe-colored suede and textile, the upper is secured with two-tone laces and accented with translucent quarter-panel netting. Orange textile lines the tongue, matching the signature Jumpman that decorates the exterior. A second Jumpman icon graces the heel overlay in grey embroidery. The mid-top rides on an off-white polyurethane midsole, featuring speckled shark-tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent herringbone-pattern rubber outsole yields superior stop-and-go traction.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Thunder (2023) (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS ‘Thunder’ brings back the coveted two-tone colorway originally released in 2006. The mid-top features a black nubuck upper with contrasting yellow accents. They land on the shoe’s molded eyelets, quarter panel and lower tongue, with the latter two components covered in black netting that reflect the AJ4’s original ’89 specs. Traditional Jumpman branding decorates the molded back tab and woven tongue tag. The sneaker rests on a yellow polyurethane midsole, enhanced with visible Air-sole cushioning and supported by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Thunder (2023)
Description: The 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Thunder’ brings back the coveted colorway originally released in 2006 (and previously reissued in 2012). The upper is draped in smooth black nubuck, contrasted by hits of yellow on the molded eyelets, quarter panel, and lower tongue, with the latter two components covered in black netting. Jumpman branding appears on the Flight tongue tag and molded heel tab. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a yellow polyurethane midsole, enhanced with an exposed Air-sole unit in the heel.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro Cement Grey
Description: The Air Jordan 2 Retro ‘White Cement’ treats Michael Jordan’s sophomore signature shoe to a simple makeover. The white leather upper features a tonal lizard-textured overlay, framed in black and grey piping and accented with a grey molded heel tab. The latter is marked with an embossed Nike wordmark, while a grey Wings logo adorns the tongue. A polyurethane midsole packs encapsulated Air-sole cushioning for a smooth ride. Inside the shoe, the sockliner displays a skyline graphic and the phrase ‘Look, Up in the Air.’

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Wizards
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Washington Wizards’ showcases a familiar design based on a PE colorway that Michael Jordan wore during his time in D.C. Featuring color blocking reminiscent of the OG ‘True Blue’ edition from 1988, the classic silhouette makes use of a white tumbled leather upper with grey elephant-print overlays at the toe and heel. Contrasting blue accents appear on the interior lining, molded eyelets, and the raised Jumpman logo that decorates the heel tab. A second Jumpman graces the tongue in copper-colored embroidery, matching the circular eyelets that dot the forefoot. The mid-top is mounted on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, equipped with a visible Air-sole heel unit and supported by a durable grey rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Olive (Women's)
Description: The Travis Scott x Women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘Olive’ presents the chart-topping rapper’s first sneaker collaboration in female sizing. The upper combines a black suede base with off-white leather overlays and olive suede Swooshes, featuring a reverse check on the lateral side and a traditional design on the opposite side. The neutral earth tones are punctuated by bold crimson accents, highlighted by woven Nike Air tongue tags and mismatched Jordan and Cactus Jack branding on each heel tab. Anchoring the low-top is a rubber cupsole that pairs vintage off-white sidewalls with an olive green rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 13 Retro Black Flint
Description: The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Black Flint’ dresses the legacy model in OG-inspired color blocking reminiscent of the ‘Flint’ colorway from 1998. Black mesh overlays dominate the upper, featuring a white leather toe box with synthetic grey suede along the midfoot and collar. A crimson Jumpman decorates the white leather tongue, while the 13’s holographic ‘cat eye’ graces the lateral ankle. Anchoring the sneaker is a panther paw outsole, fitted with white herringbone traction pods and an exposed carbon fiber shank plate.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Washed Pink (Women's)
Description: The Women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Washed Pink’ delivers a pastel colorway of the foundational silhouette. The high-top dons a white leather upper with soft suede overlays in a muted pink hue. An aged pre-yellowed finish is applied to the midsole and breathable nylon tongue, the latter accented with a woven Nike tag. Additional branding elements include a pink suede Swoosh and an off-white Wings logo stamped on the lateral ankle. Underfoot, a pink rubber outsole features a traction pattern originally designed for pivoting on the hardwood.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lucky Green
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Lucky Green’ dresses the iconic silhouette in familiar color blocking that mirrors one-half of the 2009 Air Jordan 1 ‘Defining Moments Pack,’ inspired by Michael Jordan’s 63-point playoff performance against the Boston Celtics in 1986. The high-top sports a smooth leather upper, featuring a white base with contrasting hits of black on the forefoot overlay, Swoosh, and padded collar. Lush green accents land on the heel overlay and ankle flap, marked with a retro Wings logo on the lateral side. The shoe earns its OG designation with a woven Nike tag atop the breathable nylon tongue.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Skyline
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Skyline’ takes inspiration from an iconic piece of early Michael Jordan paraphernalia — a promotional image depicting a mid-flight MJ striking his instantly familiar Jumpman pose, framed against the Chicago skyline and the sky at dusk. The latter is recreated through gradient hues in pink and lavender, executed in mismatched fashion on the textile overlays of each shoe. They’re contrasted by a leather base in a crisp white finish, along with black accents on the signature Swoosh, high-cut collar, and interior lining. A vintage off-white finish is applied to the midsole, featuring encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and reinforced by a black rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 11 Retro Low Cement Grey
Description: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low ‘Cement Grey’ showcases classic two-tone color blocking modeled after the inaugural spate of low-top releases from 2001. The upper combines white ballistic mesh with tonal webbing eyelets and a patent leather mudguard in a light grey finish. A miniature Jumpman in University Blue adorns the tongue and back heel. Underpinning the sneaker is a cushy Phylon midsole, supported by a translucent rubber outsole with grey herringbone traction pods and an exposed carbon fiber shank plate.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro SB Pine Green
Description: The Nike SB x Air Jordan 4 Retro SP ‘Pine Green’ presents a skate-ready version of the legacy silhouette. Crafted from smooth off-white leather, the upper is reinforced with a forefoot overlay in light grey suede. Contrasting green accents land on the molded eyelets and heel tab, the latter marked with embossed Nike SB branding. A crimson Jumpman on the Flight tongue tag provides an unexpected pop of color. The sneaker rides on a two-tone foam midsole, fitted with an exposed Air-sole unit in the heel and supported by a gum rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro White Cement Reimagined
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro 'White Cement Reimagined' brings back one of the original colorways, celebrating the 35th anniversary of the AJ3. Designed by Tinker Hatfield, the Reimagined iteration is built to the original 1988 specs. Returning true to form, the white leather upper pairs with elephant print overlays on the heel and toe while hits of Varsity Red appear on the lace loops and the Jumpman logo on the tongue. Nike Air is emblazoned on the back heel tab, while a visible Air unit provides lightweight cushioning. A slight hint of yellowing appears on the back heel and midsole, giving the shoe a vintage look.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro UNC University Blue
Description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro SE ‘UNC’ showcases a familiar pastel hue inspired by Michael Jordan’s alma mater. The upper is crafted from University Blue nubuck with tonal TPU eyelets, ventilated quarter-panel netting and a woven jock tag at the heel. An embroidered Jumpman decorates the tongue, rendered in a reflective silver finish for added visibility in low-light conditions. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a black polyurethane midsole, accented with speckled shark-tooth detailing and fitted with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent herringbone-traction outsole provides optimal grip.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid SE Ice Blue (2023)
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE ‘White Ice Blue’ pairs the shoe’s timeless lines with a chilly color palette. The all-leather upper merges a crisp white base with pastel blue accents on the toe box, heel and collar flap. Contrasting hits of navy land on the signature Swoosh, collar and tongue, marked with an embroidered Jumpman logo. The mid-top rides on a durable rubber cupsole, featuring an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated within a lightweight polyurethane wedge.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Doernbecher (2023)
Description: Designed by Riddhi Mahajan, the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG represents one of six footwear styles that make up Nike’s Doernbecher Freestyle XVIII collection. The classic low-top showcases vibrant hues that reflect Riddhi’s sunny worldview. Denoting the colors of a sunrise, ombre laces secure the leather upper, featuring lush green overlays, white quarter panels, and a violet Swoosh. ‘Radiate Positivity’ is printed across the lateral midfoot, while ‘Brand New Day’ is inscribed on the fluorescent green toe box. Underfoot, a translucent purple rubber outsole reveals Riddhi’s name and a daisy graphic.

Name: Jordan 6 Retro Cool Grey (TD)
Description: The Air Jordan 6 Retro TD ‘Cool Grey’ delivers a refreshed colorway of the championship silhouette built for little feet. The condensed design makes use of a grey nubuck upper with white tumbled leather overlays throughout the midfoot and collar. Embroidered Jumpman branding decorates the tongue and back heel. Plush grey textile lines the collar for a comfortable fit, while a spoiler-like pull tab provides easy on and off. A full-length foam midsole yields lightweight cushioning and a smooth ride.

Name: Jordan 6 Retro Cool Grey
Description: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Cool Grey’ brings spare, neutral tones to the classic silhouette that Michael Jordan wore when he captured the first of his six NBA championships. Accentuating the shoe’s dynamic lines is the composition of the upper, which pairs a grey nubuck foundation with leather overlays in a stark white finish. Jumpman branding adorns the lace cover and back heel, the latter captioned with embroidered ‘AIR’ lettering. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a polyurethane midsole, featuring a visible Air-sole unit in the heel and a translucent rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: Jordan 13 Retro Playoffs (2023)
Description: The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Playoff' 2023 brings back an original colorway first seen when Michael Jordan debuted it at the 1998 All-Star Game in New York City. The black quilted leather and suede upper features a hologram on the back heel, along with a Jumpman logo in a yellow circle on the tongue. Panther inspirations from MJ's black cat nickname make up the white midsole pods as well as the segmented outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Reverse Laney (Women's)
Description: The Women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Reverse Laney’ delivers a color-flipped version of an AJ1 High from 2013, featuring a two-tone palette inspired by Michael Jordan’s high school in Wilmington, North Carolina (and originally introduced via an Air Jordan 5 Retro+ from 2000). The familiar hues are deployed on an all-leather upper, highlighted by a Varsity Maize base with contrasting overlays in Game Royal. A black Wings logo is stamped on the lateral collar, while a black woven tongue tag displays crimson Nike Air branding. The high-top rides on a crisp white midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and supported by a royal blue rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Photon Dust
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro SE ‘Craft’ makes over Tinker Hatfield’s original 1989 design with upgraded materials. The legacy silhouette sports a light grey leather upper with tonal suede construction on the collar and forefoot overlay. Support wings are built with cracked leather, while gridded suede replaces traditional plastic netting on the quarter panel. Pale Vanilla accents settle on the shoe’s molded eyelets, as well as Jumpman branding hits at the tongue and heel. Lightweight cushioning is provided an off-white polyurethane midsole, featuring a visible Air-sole unit nestled in the heel.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Photon Dust (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro SE GS ‘Craft’ brings neutral tones and an elevated build to Tinker Hatfield’s original 1989 design. A subtle pale grey finish is executed on the leather upper, bolstered with a forefoot overlay in color-matched shaggy suede. Contrasting Pale Vanilla accents settle on the shoe’s molded eyelets, as well as Jumpman branding hits on the tongue tag and heel tab. In lieu of traditional netting, suede quarter panels are embellished with grid-embossed detailing. An exposed Air-sole unit enhances the white foam midsole, supported underfoot by a two-tone herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro Aqua
Description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Aqua’ showcases a distinctive color scheme that recalls an AJ5 PE made for Chris Paul during his time with the New Orleans Hornets. The legacy silhouette makes use of a black nubuck upper with translucent quarter-panel netting for improved breathability. A bright teal Jumpman decorates the back heel and silver reflective tongue. Anchoring the sneaker is a black polyurethane midsole, featuring speckled yellow shark-tooth detailing and visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel. Finished in a vibrant turquoise hue, a translucent rubber outsole yields durable traction.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Black Phantom
Description: The Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP ‘Black Phantom’ continues the Houston rapper’s remixed series centered around Michael Jordan’s debut signature shoe. This pair sports a black nubuck upper with tonal suede overlays and contrast white stitching throughout. Scott’s signature reverse Swoosh decorates the lateral side, while the opposite side features a traditional Swoosh accompanied by Cactus Jack branding. Mismatched heel tabs display a retro Wings logo on the right shoe and an embroidered bee motif on the left. The low-top is mounted on a black rubber cupsole with stitched sidewall construction and encapsulated Air-sole cushioning.

Name: Jordan 11 Retro Cherry (2022)
Description: The Air Jordan 11 Retro ‘Cherry’ showcases familiar two-tone color blocking that recalls the low-top AJ11 ‘Varsity Red’ from 2001. The upper is crafted from white ballistic mesh with tonal webbing eyelets and a shiny patent leather mudguard in a bold scarlet hue. Matching red accents land on the interior collar and an embroidered Jumpman on the white leather heel overlay. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a plush Phylon midsole, supported underfoot by a carbon fiber spring plate and a translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Crimson Bliss (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the DJ Khaled x Air Jordan 5 Retro GS ‘Crimson Bliss’ is taken from the ‘We The Best’ collection, comprising vibrant colorways of the classic silhouette that was introduced to the world by Mars Blackmon. A radiant pink hue is executed on the leather upper, equipped with quarter panel netting, a slimmed-down collar, and a quilted blue liner for a luxurious touch. An embroidered Jumpman logo adorns a reflective silver tongue, while the heel overlay features mismatched Nike Air and ‘We The Best’ branding. Speckled shark-tooth detailing enlivens the off-white foam midsole, fitted with visible Air-sole cushioning and supported by a translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 6 Retro Chrome Metallic Silver
Description: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Chrome’ showcases a familiar design previously seen on the ‘Chrome’ Air Jordan 6 Low from 2015. The upper is crafted from solid black nubuck with silver Jumpman branding on the lace guard. Standard AJ6 details remain intact, including a windowed tongue, lace locks, and a spoiler-like heel tag. The mid-top is mounted on a black polyurethane midsole, accented with metallic silver detailing and supported by a translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro A Ma Maniére Violet Ore
Description: The A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Violet Ore’ delivers an elevated take on the legacy silhouette. The Atlanta-based retailer dresses the mid-top in a muted purple nubuck upper, accented with tonal quarter panel netting and a decorative chrome rivet embedded in the lateral collar. Woven Flight tongue tags display mismatched Jumpman and A Ma Maniére branding, while molded black heel tabs feature a raised Nike Air logo. Inscribed across the interior side of each heel tab is the phrase ‘It’s not about the shoes … it’s about where you’re going.’ Quilted textile lines the collar and insole for a comfortable fit. The sneaker rides on a cream-colored polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Chicago Lost and Found
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Chicago Lost & Found’ brings back the iconic silhouette that started it all. Featuring the high-cut shape of the original 1985 release, the leather upper combines a white base with a black signature Swoosh and scarlet overlays at the forefoot and heel. Cracked black leather appears on the padded collar, while a vintage pre-yellowed finish is applied to the white rubber midsole. The vintage ‘80s aesthetic extends to the special packaging, highlighted by a damaged box plastered with sale stickers and topped with a mismatched replacement lid. An accompanying sales invoice is emblematic of a time when the Air Jordan 1 lingered on the shelves of mom and pop stores, eventually making their way into the hands of lucky customers at a steep discount.  Limited-edition poster included with all orders, while supplies last.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Chicago Lost and Found (PS)
Description: Offered in preschool sizing, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS ‘Chicago Lost & Found’ showcases a vintage aesthetic that simulates the look of an original 1985 AJ1, recovered from a forgotten corner of a mom and pop store’s dusty stockroom. Cracked white leather is utilized on the upper, contrasted by crimson overlays and a slightly larger black Swoosh. Cracked black leather appears on the padded high-cut collar, while breathable nylon is utilized on the tongue. The latter is embellished with a red woven Nike tag. Underpinning the sneaker is a durable cupsole, featuring aged white sidewalls and a crimson rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 12 Retro A Ma Maniére Black
Description: The A Ma Maniére x Wmns Air Jordan 12 Retro SP ‘Black’ brings a premium build to one of the most performance driven models in Jordan Brand’s heritage lineup. Waxed rope laces secure the black nubuck upper, accented with radiating stitched lines and bolstered with shaggy suede overlays in a rich burgundy hue. Mismatched branding decorates each tongue, highlighted by a molded Jumpman on the right shoe and A Ma Maniére’s ‘A’ logo on the left. Similar to the Atlanta retailer’s previous Jordan collaborations, quilted textile lines the interior for an elevated look and feel. Underfoot, a dark maroon rubber outsole is equipped with an exposed carbon fiber spring plate and herringbone traction pods in a crisp white finish.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Zion Williamson Voodoo
Description: The Zion Williamson x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘Voodoo’ shares a New Orleans-inspired theme with a companion Zion 2 colorway from June 2022. Braided rope laces secure the upper, featuring beige suede quarter panels and a brown suede toe box. Burlap-like overlays feature raw edges and mismatched color blocking in light brown, Oil Green and Fossil. In addition to exposed deco stitching, unique accents include an inverted mini-Swoosh on the forefoot and an embroidered voodoo-doll graphic on the lateral heel. An upside-down Wings logo is stamped on the brown suede heel tab, which lifts up to reveal mismatched ‘Voodoo’ and ‘Zion’ graphics on the interior side.

Name: Jordan 7 Retro  Trophy Room New Sheriff in Town
Description: The Trophy Room x Air Jordan 7 Retro ‘New Sheriff in Town’ celebrates the championship silhouette’s 30th anniversary with a collaboration inspired by the ’92 Barcelona Games. The patriotic design nods to the original ‘Olympic’ Air Jordan 7, while the shoe’s moniker echoes a playfully taunting one-liner that Michael Jordan leveled at Magic Johnson and Larry Bird after an infamous Dream Team scrimmage. The suede upper features a crimson base with ivory overlays, a navy neoprene tongue, and multicolor heel tabs that reference the Olympic rings. Gilded accents — highlighted by a molded Jumpman and mismatched heel badges that display the Trophy Room logo with MJ’s Olympic jersey number — symbolize the Dream Team’s gold medal run. Additional special features include His Airness’ signature etched on the lateral heel and ‘New Sheriff in Town’ embroidered on the interior tongue.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy (GS)
Description: Offered in big kid sizing, the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS ‘Midnight Navy’ features the heritage details that allowed the original 1989 design to soar. The legacy silhouette dons a white tumbled leather upper, accented with molded navy eyelets and a Jumpman-branded heel tab in a speckled grey finish. Matching grey wings provide structural support, while quarter panel netting delivers improved breathability. Atop the tongue, a woven Jumpman tag is captioned with a Flight logo in Fire Red. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit nestled in the heel.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Midnight Navy’ dresses the legacy silhouette in the same color blocking used on the OG ‘Fire Red’ colorway.
