The upper is constructed from white leather with black support wings, a matching black heel tab with embossed Jumpman branding, and navy molded eyelets. A second Jumpman icon adorns the woven tongue tag in crimson. The sneaker rides on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, featuring encapsulated Air in the forefoot and a visible unit in the heel.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Starfish (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 1 High OG ‘Starfish’ brings back the signature hue unfailingly tied to the ‘Shattered Backboard’ colorway from 2015. The all-leather upper features a white base, contrasting orange overlays, and a high-cut collar in chocolate brown. A woven Nike Air tag embellishes a lightly padded nylon tongue in a vintage off-white finish. The aged aesthetic is repeated on the rubber midsole, fitted with an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel and supported underfoot by an orange rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Canyon Purple (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Canyon Purple’ treats Tinker Hatfield’s 1989 design to a comprehensive makeover. Replacing the shoe’s traditional leather or nubuck build, the upper is crafted from shaggy suede in a vibrant purple finish. Lime green accents land on the speckled eyelets and midsole, while the signature Jumpman logo graces the woven tongue tag in Safety Orange. The bright hues are offset by contrasting hits of black on the molded wings, Jumpman-embossed heel tab, and herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro SE Black Canvas
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro SE ‘Black Canvas’ features a neutral color scheme that calls to mind Eminem’s extremely rare Carhartt x Air Jordan 4. The mid-top carries a black canvas upper with a tonal suede forefoot overlay and grey molded eyelets. A matching grey Jumpman decorates the back heel and woven tongue tag, the latter accented with a crimson Flight logo for a sharp burst of contrasting color. The sneaker rides on a two-tone polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Black Canvas (GS)
Description: Crafted for big kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro SE GS ‘Black Canvas’ transforms the legacy silhouette with a revamped build. In lieu of a traditional leather or nubuck build, the upper is draped in black canvas with a tonal suede forefoot overlay and ventilated netting on the quarter panel. The monochrome finish is disrupted by light grey molded eyelets and a matching Jumpman logo on the heel tab. Atop the tongue, a woven Jumpman tag is captioned with ‘Flight’ branding in crimson script. Visible Air-sole cushioning enhances a polyurethane midsole, supported by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro J Balvin
Description: The J Balvin x Air Jordan 2 Retro delivers the Colombian reggaeton singer’s whimsical take on the legacy silhouette, featuring a powder blue ripstop upper with contrast multicolor stitching. A glow-in-the-dark Wings logo adorns the tongue, while an all-over graphic depicting cloudy blue skies decorates the interior lining and heel overlay. The latter is further accented with J Balvin’s signature smiley face graphic. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a crisp white polyurethane midsole, fitted with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and supported by a translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Fire Red (2022)
Description: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Fire Red’ brings back an OG colorway of the first Air Jordan model designed by Tinker Hatfield. Originally released in 1988, the sneaker carries a white leather upper with dark grey elephant-print overlays at the forefoot and heel. Contrasting crimson accents settle on the perforated leather collar, molded eyelets, and polyurethane midsole, featuring a visible Air-sole unit nestled in the heel. Matching hits of Fire Red distinguish the sneaker’s branding elements, including a Jumpman logo embroidered on the tongue and ‘Nike Air’ embossed on the heel.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid Sneaker School Game Winner (GS)
Description: Built for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Mid GS ‘Game Winner’ spotlights Michael Jordan’s standout achievement before he went pro. In a nod to the athlete’s alma mater, the mid-top carries a leather upper in white and University Blue. The translucent Jumpman tongue tag resembles a basketball backboard, while a netting-like overlay atop the tongue continues the playful hoops theme. The sneaker’s lateral side displays black and white graphics that depict MJ scoring the winning shot of the 1982 NCAA Championship, while his UNC coach Dean Smith looks on from the sidelines.

Name: Jordan 1 Low Triple White (2022)
Description: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 1 Low ‘Triple White’ brings a blank-slate aesthetic to a streamlined silhouette modeled after the 1985 original. A pristine white finish is applied to the leather upper, yielding a versatile and highly adaptive design. Tonal branding elements include an embroidered Jumpman on the tongue and a stitched Wings logo on the back heel. The sneaker is mounted on a traditional white rubber cupsole, featuring an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in lightweight polyurethane.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Desert Elephant
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Desert Elephant’ showcases materials and color blocking that stay true to the iconic silhouette’s original 1988 release. The upper is constructed from black tumbled leather with signature elephant-print overlays in a light tan finish. The neutral hue is repeated on the collar, eyestay, and tongue, the latter accented with a crimson Jumpman logo. Supporting the mid-top is a white polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit nestled under the heel.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Black Dark Powder Blue
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘UNC’ continues a tradition of classic Jordan models draped in colors that pay homage to Michael Jordan’s alma mater. This pair utilizes a leather upper that combines a white base with contrasting black accents on the forefoot overlay and signature Swoosh. The heel panel is finished in Dark Powder Blue, matching the rubber outsole and woven Nike Air tongue tag. A retro Wings logo on the heel tab maintains the shoe’s OG aesthetic.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Reverse Mocha
Description: The Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘Reverse Mocha’ delivers a twist on the original ‘Mocha’ AJ1 Low from 2019. The upper combines a brown suede base with ivory leather overlays and the Houston rapper’s signature reverse Swoosh on the lateral side, featuring oversized dimensions and a neutral cream finish. Contrasting scarlet accents distinguish a pair of woven Nike Air tongue tags, as well as mismatched Cactus Jack and retro Wings logos embroidered on each heel tab. A vintage off-white rubber midsole is bolstered with encapsulated Nike Air cushioning in the heel and a brown rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Reverse Mocha (TD)
Description: Built for little feet, the Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Low OG TD ‘Reverse Mocha’ presents a color-flipped iteration of the Houston rapper’s ‘Dark Mocha’ Jordan 1 Low from 2019. An oversized reverse Swoosh adorns a brown nubuck upper with off-white leather overlays. Contrasting hits of crimson arrive via the sneaker’s branding elements, including a woven Nike tongue tag and mismatched heel tabs, featuring the Cactus Jack face graphic on the left shoe and the Jordan Wings logo on the right. A cream-colored midsole enhances the shoe’s vintage aesthetic.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Reverse Mocha (PS)
Description: Made for little kids, the Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Low OG PS ‘Reverse Mocha’ presents a color-flipped rendition of the Houston rapper’s original ‘Mocha’ Jordan 1 Low from 2019. The upper is crafted from brown nubuck with off-white leather overlays and an oversized reverse Swoosh on the lateral side. A woven Nike Air tag — along with an off-center Cactus Jack label — adorns the tongue, while crimson embroidery on each heel tab displays Travis Scott’s face graphic on left shoe and the Jordan Wings logo on the right. An aged finish distinguishes the midsole, reinforced underfoot by a grippy brown rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 Low OG Bleached Coral
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘Bleached Coral’ brings a pastel pop of color to the classic silhouette. The low-top dons a mixed-material upper, highlighted by a white leather quarter panel, black cracked leather on the forefoot overlay, and pink suede on the perforated toe box. Additional hits of pink suede land on the heel overlay and back tab, featuring a contrasting black Wings logo. The sneaker is mounted on a traditional rubber cupsole with a hidden Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in lightweight polyurethane.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid White University Gold (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘University Gold’ presents a sunny colorway of the timeless silhouette. The mid-top makes use of an all-leather upper, highlighted by a stark white base with yellow accents on the collar, Swoosh, and forefoot and heel overlay. A Jumpman icon graces the woven tongue tag, while a retro Wings logo is stamped on the lateral ankle. The sneaker rides on a rubber cupsole, featuring encapsulated Air-sole cushioning in the heel and a grippy traction pattern underfoot.

Name: Jordan 1 Low Tie-Dye
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Low SE ‘Tie Dye’ takes an essential colorway of the classic silhouette and adds bright infusions of color for a summer-ready take on the 1985 original. The low-top features traditional ‘Black Toe’ color blocking, highlighted by a white leather base with contrasting black accents on the Swoosh and forefoot overlay. A stitched Wings logo accompanies a tie dye-like print on each heel overlay, featuring a mostly violet finish on the right shoe and aqua coloring on the left. The latter hue is repeated on the grippy rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Infrared (GS)
Description: Built for big kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS ‘Infrared’ adds color-popped accents to an otherwise neutral colorway of the vintage silhouette designed by Tinker Hatfield. The color blocking is reminiscent of the ‘Green Glow’ Air Jordan 4 from 2013, and features a dark grey nubuck upper with solid black accents on the quarter panel netting, structural wings, and Jumpman-branded heel piece. A lighter shade of grey distinguishes the forefoot overlay, while vibrant hits of Infrared settle on the molded eyelets and woven Jumpman tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning arrives via an exposed Air-sole unit nestled in the heel of the two-tone midsole.

Name: Jordan 6 Retro Red Oreo
Description: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Red Oreo’ brings a simplistic two-tone palette to the classic silhouette that Michael Jordan wore when he clinched the first of his six NBA championships. The mid-top sports a white leather upper with perforated detailing and a tonal Jumpman logo embroidered on the back heel. Covered in white speckles, crimson accents appear on the molded pull tab and polyurethane midsole, featuring an exposed Air-sole unit in the heel and a translucent rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Military Black
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Military Black’ showcases the same color blocking and materials featured on the OG ‘Military Blue’ colorway from 1989. Smooth white leather is utilized on the upper, bolstered with a forefoot overlay in grey suede. Contrasting black accents make their way to the TPU eyelets, molded heel tab, and the Jumpman logo displayed on the woven tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a two-tone polyurethane midsole, enhanced with a visible Air-sole unit under the heel.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Neapolitan Dark Mocha (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Neapolitan’ enlivens the legacy silhouette with pastel pops of color. The mid-top carries a white tumbled leather upper with signature elephant-print overlays in Dark Mocha. Jumpman branding decorates the tongue and back heel in contrasting pink and brown hues. A vintage off-white finish is applied to the traditional polyurethane midsole, featuring visible Air-sole cushioning and a glossy splash of Atmosphere Pink at the heel.

Name: Jordan 11 Retro Low 72-10
Description: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low ‘72-10’ brings back a celebratory design theme first featured on an Air Jordan 11 release from 2015. Like its predecessor, this pair nods to the Chicago Bulls’ legendary 1996-96 season, when Michael Jordan led the team to a record-breaking 72-10 record. Rendered in low-top form, the sneaker makes use of a black tumbled leather upper with a tonal patent leather mudguard. Crimson Jumpman branding delivers color-popped accents on the tongue and heel. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a white Phylon midsole, fitted with full-length Air-sole cushioning and supported by a translucent rubber midsole. The Jordan 11 Low '72-10' will release on May 14, 2022.

Name: Jordan 6 Retro Midnight Navy (2022)
Description: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Midnight Navy’ brings back a classic two-tone colorway initially released in 2000. The legacy silhouette sports a white leather upper with perforated detailing throughout the midfoot and collar. Navy blue accents land on the signature windowed tongue, molded heel tab, and the Jumpman branding hits that decorate the lace guard and back heel. The sneaker rides on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, enhanced with a visible Air-sole heel unit and supported by a translucent rubber outsole. The Jordan 6 'Midnight Navy' 2022 will release on May 11, 2022.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid Light Curry Cardinal
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘Light Curry Cardinal Red’ features warm hues on a classic silhouette inspired by the 1985 original. The leather upper combines a crisp white base with pastel beige overlays and bold scarlet accents on the signature Swoosh and mid-cut collar. A red Wings logo adorns the lateral ankle, while Jumpman branding makes its way to the tongue tag and sockliner. The sneaker sits on a rubber cupsole, highlighted by white sidewalls and a grippy black rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid Light Smoke Grey Anthracite
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘Light Smoke Grey’ features an understated palette entirely devoid of color. The mid-top makes use of a smooth leather upper that combines a white base with light grey overlays at the forefoot and heel. Contrasting hits of black settle on the mid-cut collar and signature Swoosh, the latter accented with contrast white stitching. Additional branding hits take the form of a Jumpman icon on the woven tongue tag and a retro Wings logo on the lateral ankle. Anchoring the sneaker is a durable rubber cupsole with an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in lightweight polyurethane.

Name: Jordan 1 Low Bulls
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Low ‘Reverse Black Toe’ delivers a flipped colorway of the iconic OG colorway from 1985. The Chicago-inspired design features a leather upper that combines a crisp white base with Gym Red accents on the forefoot overlay and signature Swoosh. Contrasting hits of black land on the low-cut collar and heel overlay, marked with retro Wings logo in crimson embroidery. Jumpman branding adorns the tongue and sockliner. The low-top is mounted on a durable rubber cupsole, fitted with an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Muslin
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro SE ‘Muslin’ updates Tinker Hatfield’s original 1988 design with a recrafted build. In lieu of traditional leather, the upper is constructed from Muslin canvas with forefoot and heel overlays in Cement Grey suede. University Red accents land on the sneaker’s lower eyelets, as well as Jumpman branding hits atop the tongue and molded heel panel. The sneaker rides on an off-white polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel. Underfoot, a durable grey rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Blank Canvas (Women's)
Description: The Women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Blank Canvas’ presents an undyed design ready-made for customization. The layered upper is constructed from off-white canvas, featuring raw edges and tonal stitching. Molded eyelets and embroidered Jumpman branding at the tongue and heel maintain the shoe’s one-note finish. An ivory-hued polyurethane midsole packs a visible Air-sole unit in the heel for lightweight cushioning. Underfoot, the herringbone-traction rubber outsole is accented with multi-color paint splashes.

Name: Jordan 1 Low Game Royal Blue Void (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 1 Low ‘Game Royal’ brings vibrant tones to a classic silhouette based on the original 1985 release. The leather upper features a Blue Void base with Game Royal overlays and a light grey Swoosh. Branding elements include a Jumpman icon on the tongue, an embroidered ‘23’ on the lace keeper, and a stitched Wings logo on the heel overlay. The low-top rides on a traditional rubber cupsole, highlighted by white sidewalls and a navy rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Rebellionaire
Description: The Air Jordan 1 High OG ‘Rebellionaire’ showcases a unique design that ties into the shoe’s mythic ‘Banned’ narrative, wherein Michael Jordan incurred a $5,000 fine each time the rookie wore his signature black and red kicks on the court — a violation of the NBA’s uniform dress code at the time. The iconic high-top features a leather upper finished in two-tone color blocking reminiscent of the OG ‘Shadow’ colorway. Unique details include the ‘Banned’ AJ1’s red ‘X’ on the heel, along with an all-over print that spells out ‘They Can’t Stop You From Wearing Them,’ which paraphrases a line from an original Air Jordan 1 TV commercial from 1985.

Name: Jordan 12 Retro Playoffs (2022)
Description: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Playoff’ brings back the shoe that Michael Jordan wore during his 1997 championship run. The mid-top sports an essential two-tone color scheme, featuring radiating stitched lines on the black leather upper and lizard-textured overlays in a contrasting white finish. The sneaker’s molded eyelets shine in metallic silver, while color-popped crimson accents land on the Jumpman-embroidered tongue and webbing heel loop. Performance benefits include full-length Zoom Air cushioning, a carbon fiber shank plate, and a rubber outsole with herringbone traction pods under the forefoot and heel.

Name: Jordan 6 Retro UNC White
Description: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘UNC Home’ features a familiar color combination that pays homage to MJ’s alma mater. The iconic silhouette carries a white leather upper with nubuck underlays in University Blue. Contrasting navy accents make their way to the molded TPU heel tab, textile collar lining and polyurethane midsole, the latter enhanced with visible Air-sole cushioning. Reflective perforations provide added visibility in low-light conditions, while a woven jock tag at the heel nods to the shoe’s varsity athletics theme.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Cardinal Red
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Cardinal Red’ showcases a distinctive palette influenced by an OG colorway of the Air Jordan 7. The sneaker’s titular hue appears on the collar lining, molded eyelets, and raised Jumpman branding at the heel, all of which are contrasted by a white tumbled leather upper. A second Jumpman icon adorns the tongue in orange embroidery, while the 3’s signature elephant print overlays reinforce the forefoot and heel. The mid-top is mounted on a two-tone polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit nestled under the heel.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Dark Marina Blue
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Dark Marina Blue’ dresses the iconic silhouette in classic two-tone color blocking. The all-leather upper features a black base with contrasting dark blue overlays along the forefoot, heel, collar and eyestay. A matching blue Swoosh is accompanied by a Jordan Wings logo stamped in black on the lateral collar flap. Atop the nylon tongue, a woven Nike Air tag nods to the shoe’s retro cushioning technology: an Air-sole unit encapsulated in polyurethane nestled in the heel of the rubber cupsole.

Name: Jordan 5 Low Girls That Hoop (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 5 Retro Low ‘Girls That Hoop’ updates the classic silhouette with refreshed materials and colors. The low-top makes use of a pink nubuck upper with molded eyelets and OG plastic lace locks. A TPU grille reveals a reflective finish on the quarter panel underlay. The sneaker sits atop a red polyurethane midsole with black shark tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid Diamond Shorts
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE ‘Diamond’ dresses the classic silhouette in a simple two-tone palette celebrating the 75th anniversary of the NBA. The mid-top carries an all-leather upper that combines a clean white base with contrasting black accents on the forefoot overlay, signature Swoosh, and mid-cut collar. The tongue tag displays classic Jumpman branding framed in a geometric shape that nods to the NBA’s diamond anniversary. A white rubber midsole features an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel and a milky white translucent rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Red Thunder
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Red Thunder’, also known as 'Crimson', features familiar color blocking that recalls the coveted ‘Thunder’ colorway, originally released in 2006 and subsequently reissued in 2012. The mid-top sports a black nubuck upper with contrasting pops of crimson in lieu of the older shoe’s Tour Yellow accents. They appear on the sneaker’s molded eyelets, interior tongue, quarter panel, throat and midsole, which packs visible Air-sole cushioning under the heel. Jumpman branding decorates the tongue tag and heel.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Patent Bred
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Patent Bred’ treats the iconic colorway to a glossy makeover. Aside from the shoe’s patent leather construction, the essential design DNA remains intact. The upper pairs basic black paneling with contrasting hits of Varsity Red on the toe box, Swoosh, heel overlay and collar flap. A woven Nike tag adorns the black nylon tongue, while a Wings logo is stamped on the lateral collar. The high-top rides on a sturdy rubber cupsole, enhanced with an Air-sole unit encapsulated in lightweight polyurethane.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Golf Bred
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Golf ‘Bred’ transforms the OG colorway with a retooled build designed for the links. The upper faithfully recreates the 1989 original, highlighted by a black nubuck upper with tonal quarter panel netting, grey TPU eyelets and red Jumpman branding on the woven tongue tag. A second Jumpman logo adorns the molded heel tab. The AJ4’s distinctive midsole comes complete with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent outsole plate features seven removable spikes for optimal grip.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Hand Crafted
Description: The Air Jordan 1 High OG ‘Crafted’ treats the iconic silhouette to an eclectic color palette. The upper features a white leather base with brown nubuck forefoot overlays, green nubuck eyestays, a magenta leather heel overlay, and reflective silver trim along the quarter panel and heel. Additional details include a stitched leather Wings logo on the lateral collar flap, two-tone dyed laces, and a standard Nike-branded woven tag atop the nylon tongue. A rubber cupsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning anchors the high-top.

Name: Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey (2021)
Description: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 11 Retro ‘Cool Grey’ brings back a colorway first released in 2001 and retroed again in 2010. Celebrating the 20th anniversary of the original launch, the mid-top build is faithful to the original, featuring a nubuck upper with tonal webbing lace loops and a shiny patent leather overlay, all rendered in tones of Medium and Cool Grey. A white Jumpman logo is embroidered on the lateral ankle, while a stylized ‘23’ decorates the heel notch. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a full-length Air-sole unit housed within a white Phylon midsole. Underfoot, a translucent outsole reveals a carbon fiber spring plate for enhanced on-court responsiveness.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid SE Dark Chocolate
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE ‘Dark Chocolate’ features rustic earth tones on a classic silhouette modeled after the 1985 original. Soft black textile lines the interior of the upper, featuring a light brown nubuck base with a black leather Swoosh and suede overlays in chocolate brown. Reflective detailing lands on the heel and laces, good for enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. The mid-top rides on an Air-assisted rubber cupsole, highlighted by off-white sidewalls and a black rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid Linen
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘College Grey’ applies a neutral two-tone palette to a classic silhouette inspired by Peter Moore’s original 1985 design. The all-leather upper features a clean white base with contrasting overlays in a refined tan hue. Jumpman branding decorates the sockliner and woven tongue tag, while a retro Wings graces the lateral collar flap. The mid-top rests on a sturdy rubber cupsole, which houses an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in lightweight polyurethane.

Name: Jordan 1 Low SE Light Curry
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Low SE ‘Ceramic’ applies refined earth tones to a low-profile silhouette modeled after the 1985 original. The upper combines an off-white canvas base with orange suede overlays and an olive green suede Swoosh. The latter hue makes repeat appearances on the interior collar and the Jumpman logo embroidered on the tongue. A second Jumpman icon is stamped on the insole, while stitched Wings branding decorates the heel overlay. Underfoot, a gum rubber outsole provides sticky traction.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro Low SP Off-White Black Blue
Description: With the release of the Off-White x Air Jordan 2 Retro Low SP ‘Black Varsity Royal’, a relatively unheralded silhouette gets the Virgil Abloh treatment. The low-top carries a black leather upper with a tonal lizard-textured overlay and contrasting royal blue accents. They land on the molded heel panel, midfoot piping and exposed-foam tongue, featuring the Jordan Wings logo for an OG touch. Michael Jordan’s signature is scrawled across the lateral side, while Abloh leaves his mark with a plastic zip tie, medial-side Helvetica text and ‘SHOELACES’ printed on the laces. Faux cracking on the midsole gives the shoe an aged, distressed aesthetic.

Name: Jordan 14 Retro Low Shocking Pink (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 14 Retro Low ‘Shocking Pink’ gives the sleek silhouette an energetic makeover. A bold shade of fuchsia is applied to the shaggy suede upper, accented with a black Jumpman badge on the lateral side. Matching black hits make their way to the collar, tongue and Phylon midsole, featuring the 14’s toothy detailing in a bright red hue. Encapsulated Zoom Air units provide responsive cushioning in the forefoot and heel, while a carbon fiber shank plate offers improved midfoot stability. Underfoot, a translucent pink rubber outsole utilizes a herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Pine Green
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Pine Green’ combines OG-style color blocking with updated materials. Black textured nubuck replaces traditional leather construction on the upper, which is enlivened with verdant green accents on the molded eyelets, perforated leather collar, and embroidered Jumpman branding atop the tongue. Forefoot and heel overlays are rendered in the 3’s signature elephant print, while the molded heel tab displays a second Jumpman icon. The retro silhouette is mounted on a white polyurethane midsole with contrast green detailing and visible Air-sole cushioning under the heel.

Name: MSCHF Big Red Boot
Description: The MSCHF Big Red Boot presents a cartoonishly proportioned high-top from the Brooklyn-based creative collective known for whimsical and provocative footwear. A straightforward crimson hue suffuses the bulky boot, constructed with a single-mold-shell design and a sturdy TPU rubber shell. The bulbous silhouette features a padded collar that reaches midcalf, and a flat EVA outsole marked with horizontal treads and debossed MSCHF branding.

Name: New Balance 550 Aime Leon Dore Masaryk Community Gym Green
Description: The Aimé Leon Dore x New Balance 550 ‘Classic Pine’ is taken from a capsule collection inspired by New York’s Masaryk Community Gym. This pair sports a yellow-tinted leather upper with contrast green stitching throughout each overlaid panel. Green mesh is utilized on the collar and signature ‘N’ logo, while matching green textile lines the interior. Dual branding appears on the woven tongue tag and back heel. The low-top is mounted on a durable rubber cupsole, featuring yellowed sidewalls and an exposed foam wedge on the medial side.

Name: New Balance 991v2 MiUK Stone Island Black
Description: The Stone Island x New Balance 991v2 Made in England ‘Black’ features a stealthy palette inspired by industrial spaces that have been converted into venues and clubs. The upper combines black nubuck overlays with olive mesh construction that resembles latticed metal. A woven tongue patch displays Stone Island’s compass logo, while a reflective ‘N’ adorns the quarter panel. Additional reflective accents land on the vamp overlays, eyestay, and heel and foxing windows. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a full-length FuelCell midsole, fitted with an ENCAP heel and semi-translucent ABZORB SBS pods. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole reveals Stone Island’s oversized compass logo.

Name: New Balance 9060 The Whitaker Group Missing Pieces Silver Moss Green
Description: The Whitaker Group x New Balance 9060 ‘Silver Moss Green’ is taken from the ‘Missing Pieces Pack,’ featuring colorful designs inspired by the bright future envisioned by today’s younger generations. The upper is built with pale green nubuck with open-cell mesh underlays in Hazy Peach. The lifestyle runner rests on a dual-density ABZORB midsole, fitted with SBS cushioning and a translucent CR device embedded in the heel. A diamond-pattern rubber outsole, inspired by the New Balance 860, delivers lightweight traction underfoot.

Name: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Sulphur Green
Description: The Teddy Santis x New Balance 990v6 Made in USA ‘Pale Yellow’ delivers a summer-ready colorway of the lifestyle running shoe. Built with a yellow mesh base, the upper is stripped of the standard midfoot saddle, allowing the pigskin suede and synthetic overlays to flow unencumbered from heel to toe. Contrasting green accents land on the signature ‘N’ logo and New Balance 990 tongue tag. The sneaker rides on an ENCAP midsole, featuring lightweight FuelCell foam with a durable polyurethane rim.

Name: New Balance 998 MiUSA Teddy Santis Plum Purple
Description: The Teddy Santis x New Balance 998 Made in USA ‘Plum Purple’ updates the lifestyle runner with a bold splash of color. Appointed as Creative Director of New Balance’s vaunted Made in USA line in 2021, Santis dresses the heritage silhouette in a purple mesh upper with tonal suede overlays throughout. A matte silver ‘N’ logo graces the quarter panel, while a Flying NB graphic is embroidered on the heel tab. New Balance’s ABZORB midsole delivers lightweight cushioning with every step.

Name: New Balance 550 Terracotta
Description: The New Balance 550 ‘White Astro Dust’ delivers an essential two-tone colorway of a heritage hoops shoe originally released in 1989. Reintroduced to the masses in 2020, the low-top utilizes a white leather upper with a tonal suede forefoot overlay and faded red accents. They land on the shoe’s padded mesh collar, TPU heel clip, and various branding elements, which include the Flying NB logo that decorates the back heel. The sneaker rides on a sturdy cupsole, fitted with a lightweight foam wedge and underpinned by a scarlet rubber outsole.

Name: New Balance 550 White Dusty Blue
Description: The New Balance 550 ‘White Vintage Indigo’ carries a crisp white leather upper, reinforced with off-white suede overlays along the forefoot and collar. The latter is built with padded mesh in a dark indigo hue, matching the shoe’s branding elements and TPU heel clip. The retro silhouette rides on a durable cupsole, featuring stitched sidewall construction and a navy rubber outsole.

Name: New Balance 998 Ronnie Fieg & Frank Lloyd Wright Foundation Broadacre City Chutney
Description: Launching as part of the two-piece ‘Broadacre City’ pack, the Ronnie Fieg x Frank Lloyd Wright Foundation x New Balance 998 Made in USA ‘Chutney’ celebrates the 35th anniversary of the lifestyle running shoe. The collaborative design showcases rich earth tones inspired by Broadacre City, a futuristic city concept developed by renowned architect Frank Lloyd Wright. The upper combines a cream-hued mesh toe box with pigskin suede overlays in brick red and olive green. Mismatched white and pink ‘N’ logos adorn the quarter panel in shaggy tan suede, while the custom sockliner features Frank Lloyd Wright branding and a Broadacre City sketch. The sneaker rides on New Balance’s ENCAP midsole with ABZORB cushioning in the heel.

Name: New Balance 550 White Rain Cloud (Women's)
Description: The New Balance Women’s 550 ‘Rain Cloud’ pairs the shoe’s throwback lines with a refined, neutral color scheme. The retro silhouette makes use of a white leather upper with light grey accents. They settle on the signature ‘N’ logo, TPU heel counter, and the leather overlay that reinforces the padded mesh collar. New Balance 550 branding appears on the woven tongue tag, while a Flying NB logo decorates the back heel. Reflecting the model’s ‘80s basketball roots, a durable rubber cupsole anchors the low, featuring an exposed foam wedge on the medial side.

Name: New Balance 860v2 Aime Leon Dore Red
Description: Launching as part of a collaborative three-piece pack, the Aimé Leon Dore x New Balance 860v2 ‘Red’ brings back a performance running shoe originally released in 2012. The upper combines airy cream-colored mesh with durable synthetic overlays in silver and tan. A crimson ‘N’ logo adorns the red mesh quarter panel, while the tongue is marked with Aimé Leon Dore branding. The sneaker sits atop New Balance’s N-ergy midsole, featuring ABZORB cushioning in the heel and a durable rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Black Grey
Description: The New Balance 2002R ‘Black Grey’ is taken from the ‘Protection Pack,’ featuring tonal colorways and a distressed aesthetic. This pair makes use of a black mesh upper with raw-edged suede overlays in matching black and grey. A black leather ‘N’ logo outlined in white trim adorns the quarter panel, while ‘New Balance Running’ is inscribed on the exposed-foam tongue. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of an ABZORB midsole with ABZORB SBS pods in the heel.

Name: Nike Air Foamposite One Anthracite (2023)
Description: The 2023 edition of the Nike Air Foamposite One ‘Anthracite’ brings back a colorway originally released in 2007. The monochromatic silhouette features a black molded polyurethane upper with tonal nubuck trim on the eyestay and collar. Penny’s 1 Cent logo adorns the jeweled tongue tag, sockliner and back tab. In terms of performance, the concealed Phylon midsole packs a full-length Zoom Air-sole unit for lightweight cushioning. Underfoot, a herringbone traction rubber outsole provides durable traction.

Name: Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Doernbecher Hailey (Women's)
Description: Designed by Hailey Leyva, the Nike Air Max 1 ‘86 OG ‘Big Bubble’ is taken from the Doernbecher Freestyle XIX Collection. The retro runner sports a white and pink leather upper, accented with a signature Swoosh in metallic gold. Five hearts adorn the toe box, hand-drawn by Hailey and representing each member of her family. An anatomical heart graphic appears on the tongue, nodding to Hailey’s medical journey, while squiggly lines on the midsole symbolize the calm of ocean waves. Underfoot, gold glitter enlivens a pink-tinged translucent rubber outsole. The kicks come with a detachable bracelet, festooned with ten charms reflecting a collection of Hailey’s favorite things.

Name: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Reverse Grinch
Description: The Nike Zoom Kobe 6 Protro ‘Reverse Grinch’ delivers a color-flipped version of the iconic ‘Grinch’ colorway from 2010. A bright crimson hue is executed on the scaly micro-mesh upper, secured with neon green laces and accented with a contrasting black Swoosh. A padded low-cut collar allows for a full range of motion, while a molded TPU heel counter provides rearfoot stability. The sneaker sits on a lightweight Cushlon midsole with a springy Zoom Air unit nestled in the forefoot.

Name: Nike SB Dunk Low TIGHTBOOTH
Description: The TIGHTBOOTH x Nike Dunk Low SB presents the Japanese brand’s take on the classic silhouette. The low-top carries a black suede upper with textured white leather overlays at the forefoot and heel. On the lateral side, an orange TIGHTBOOTH tag is appended to the reflective black leather Swoosh. Dual logos adorn the stuffed tongue, while orange insoles display mismatched TIGHTBOOTH and Nike SB branding. The sneaker is mounted on a black rubber midsole, contrasted underfoot by a grippy white rubber outsole.

Name: Nike NOCTA Glide Drake White Chrome
Description: The NOCTA x Nike Glide ‘Triple White’ delivers a clean colorway of the lifestyle silhouette based on the Zoom Flight 95 basketball shoe. The upper combines breathable white mesh with woven textile on the midfoot overlay. The latter is accented with a molded mini-Swoosh, while a jeweled NOCTA logo adorns the tongue. The sneaker rides on a bulky Phylon midsole, featuring Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot and unique ‘bug eye’ detailing embedded in the sidewall.

Name: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Premium University of Oregon PE
Description: The Nike Air Force 1 ’07 Premium ‘University of Oregon’ PE features a white leather upper offset with reflective piping. Textured suede accents in a warm shade of green recall the grass of football fields. A “Ducks of a Feather” wordmark appears on the cork sockliner, with the “Oregon O” embroidered on the heel. The sneaker includes a hang tag featuring similar motifs in metallic gold. The midsole is rendered in Sail, lending the shoe a pre-aged aesthetic. Underfoot, a light grey rubber outsole utilizes the original pivot-point traction pattern. Produced in a limited run of 2,200 units in partnership with Division Street’s Ducks of a Feather, each pair is housed in a specially designed Go Ducks box. Proceeds benefit participating University of Oregon student-athletes.

Name: Nike Air Zoom Courtposite Supreme Metallic Gold
Description: The Supreme x Nike Air Zoom Courtposite ‘Metallic Gold’ is taken from a three-piece footwear pack made exclusively for the New York skate brand. An iridescent metallic gold finish is applied to the molded Posite upper, accented with a Supreme wordmark across the lateral eyestay and bolstered with forefoot overlay in durable black rubber. Contrasting crimson accents settle on the dual-branded sockliner and the welded Supreme logo that graces the tongue. Underfoot, the black rubber outsole reveals a silver-plated TPU shank for midfoot stability.

Name: Wmns Sabrina 1 'Grounded'
Description: The Nike Women’s Sabrina 1 ‘Grounded’ dresses Sabrina Ionescu’s debut signature shoe in a subtle palette punctuated by vibrant pops of color. The low-top employs an embroidered textile upper in a Light Bone finish. On the lateral side, an embroidered Swoosh in Ashen Slate is stitched atop a midfoot panel made with translucent mesh. Contrasting hits of Laser Orange land on the tongue tag, which is marked with a circular patch bearing Sabrina’s personal logo. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a full-length Nike React midsole with a top-loaded Zoom Air unit in the forefoot.

Name: Nike SB Dunk High Sweet Tooth Candy Corn
Description: The Nike Dunk High SB ‘Sweet Tooth’ takes inspiration from candy corn, the perennial Halloween treat. The leather upper combines a white forefoot with a gradient blend of orange and yellow across the midfoot and heel. Teeth mark indentations are found on the toe box, while the Nike SB tongue tag features a cautionary message on the interior side that reminds wearers, ‘Do Not Take Candy From Strangers.’ Inside the shoe, custom insoles display an all-over print made up of the cone-shaped confection.

Name: Nike Dunk Low Vintage Panda (Women's)
Description: The Nike Women’s Dunk Low ‘Vintage Panda’ showcases an aged aesthetic, thanks to the rubber midsole appearing in a vintage off-white finish. Up top, the retro silhouette makes use of a smooth leather build, featuring a crisp white base with contrasting black overlays and a color-matched Swoosh. A woven Nike tag adorns the nylon tongue, while an embroidered Nike wordmark appears on the back tab. Undergirding the sneaker is a grippy rubber outsole in a solid black finish.

Name: Nike Air Max Plus Patta FC Barcelona Culers del Món
Description: The Patta x Nike Air Max Plus ‘Home Kit’ dresses the retro runner in the signature colors of FC Barcelona. Finished in a gradient blend of navy and magenta, the mesh upper features dual Swoosh branding and a black TPU cage inspired by palm trees swaying in the wind. In addition to the traditional Tn badge at the heel, branding elements include Patta Air tongue tags, FC Barcelona lace jewels, and ‘Culers del Mon’ inscribed on the sockliner. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a two-tone polyurethane midsole, equipped with a whale tail-inspired shank and visible Air-sole units in the forefoot and heel.

Name: Nike Dunk Low Polar Blue
Description: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Polar Blue’ features a crisp white base with steel blue overlays and a color-matched Swoosh. Heritage details include breathable perforations on the toe box and a breathable nylon tongue, topped with a woven Nike tag. Additional Nike branding appears on the back tab and sockliner. Reflecting the shoe’s ‘80s roots is a durable rubber cupsole, fitted with an interior polyurethane wedge for lightweight cushioning.

Name: Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh
Description: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Smoke Grey Gum’ features reflective threads woven into the laces, which secure a white leather upper with grey suede overlays at the forefoot and heel. A reflective grey leather Swoosh sweeps across the side panel. Additional branding elements include a woven Nike tongue tag and an embroidered Nike wordmark on the back tab. The sneaker rests on a crisp white midsole, supported underfoot by a grippy gum rubber outsole.

Name: Nike SB Dunk Low Born X Raised One Block At A Time
Description: The Born x Raised x Nike Dunk Low SB ‘One Block at a Time’ brings a raft of unique details to the classic silhouette. The LA-based streetwear brand outfits the upper in textured white leather with ornate perforations on the toe box and contrasting nubuck overlays in Dodger blue. ‘One Block at a Time’ is inscribed across the toe of each shoe, while a decorative emblem in pink embroidery decorates the lateral heel. A holographic effect enlivens the Swoosh and back tab, marked with a lenticular Born SB logo. The sneaker sits atop a white rubber midsole, featuring embossed lettering that spells out ‘On the Turf’ across the heel. Underfoot, the semi-translucent blue rubber outsole reveals oversized Born SB branding.

Name: Nike Air Max 1 Familia
Description: The Nike Air Max 1 ‘Familia’ celebrates young Latina women with a colorful interpretation of the lifestyle running shoe. A pink Swoosh in textured textile adorns the upper, crafted from tan leather and outlined in red piping with yellow deco stitching. Outlined in green textile trim, the suede mudguard is rendered in a vibrant pink hue, matching the Nike Air logo stamped on the back heel. ‘Familia’ branding appears on the right tongue tag and sockliner. The sneaker rides on an off-white polyurethane midsole, fitted with visible Air-sole cushioning and supported by a multicolor rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Full Force Low White Black Pewter
Description: The Nike Full Force Low ‘White Black’ features neutral tones on a new lifestyle model that takes inspiration from the Air Force 3. White leather is utilized on the upper, accented with a black Swoosh and fortified with a grey leather overlay around the collar. A throwback Force logo is emblazoned on the black nylon tongue, while embroidered Nike branding adorns the back heel. The sneaker rests on sturdy cupsole tooling, highlighted by vintage off-white sidewalls and a black rubber outsole.

Name: Nike SB Dunk Low Albino & Preto
Description: The Albino & Preto x Nike Dunk Low SB ‘Jiu-Jitsu’ delivers the Brazilian jiu-jitsu brand’s refined take on the classic skate silhouette. The low-top sports a light tan textile upper, featuring pearl weave construction traditionally used on jiu-jitsu uniforms. A black Swoosh with contrast white stitching decorates the side panel, while Albino & Presto’s AP logo graces the back tab. Anchoring the sneaker is a durable cupsole that pairs crisp white sidewalls with a grippy black rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Korea World Make
Description: Launching as part of the ‘World Make’ collection, the Nike Air Max 1 ‘86 OG ‘Big Bubble’ takes inspiration from Korean craftsmanship. Neutral off-white tones are executed on the upper, composed of breathable hemp with woven textile paneling outlined in black trim. Tonal leather detailing appears on the signature Swoosh and mudguard. Inside the right shoe, a cork insole displays printed text that reads ‘Designed for sport. Crafted for life. World Make.’ The sneaker rests on a polyurethane midsole, featuring a large-volume Air unit inspired by the 1986 original AM1.

Name: Nike Air Max 1 '86 Big Bubble Obsidian
Description: The Nike Air Max 1 ‘86 OG ‘Big Bubble’ in ‘Obsidian’ showcases a large-volume Air-sole unit that is inspired from the first production run of the classic running shoe. The groundbreaking cushioning technology is framed within a lightweight polyurethane midsole, supported by a tri-tone waffle-traction rubber outsole. The upper takes inspiration from one of the earliest AM1 colorways, featuring a white mesh base with grey synthetic suede overlays along the midfoot and heel. Obsidian accents appear on the Swoosh and mudguard, while contrasting hits of scarlet land on the molded eyelets and Nike Air heel embroidery.

Name: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's)
Description: The Nike Women’s Dunk Low Next Nature ‘Blue Tint’ is crafted from 20% recycled content by weight. The low-top features a synthetic leather upper that combines a white base with pale blue overlays at the forefoot and heel. Nike’s retro Sunburst logo graces the Volt-colored sockliner, while standard Nike branding hits decorate the woven tongue tag and back tab. An aged off-white finish is applied to the midsole, supported underfoot by a light blue rubber outsole.

Name: Nike SB Dunk Low Supreme Rammellzee
Description: The Supreme x Nike Dunk Low SB ‘Rammellzee’ reunites the NYC skate brand with the late artist known for his graffiti writing and multi-media sculptures. The collaboration centers around the Dunk Low silhouette, featuring a canvas upper covered in Rammellzee’s original designs. Durable black suede is utilized on the eyestay, Swoosh and forefoot overlay, matching the shoe’s padded mesh tongue and textile collar lining. Gleaming accents arrive via ‘Supreme’ lace dubrae in a metallic gold finish. Anchoring the sneaker is a durable cupsole that pairs black sidewalls with a gum rubber outsole.

Name: Nike SB Dunk Low Yuto Horigome
Description: The Yuto Horigome x Nike Dunk Low SB delivers the Japanese professional skateboarder’s take on the classic silhouette. The low-top makes use of a white leather upper, fortified with grey suede overlays at the forefoot and heel. In addition to a leather Swoosh in a different shade of grey, branding elements include a cross-feather graphic on the lateral heel and Horigome’s name appended to the Nike SB tongue tag. A Nike wordmark is embroidered on the pink suede back tab, contrasted by a low-cut padded collar in brown suede. Anchoring the sneaker is a durable cupsole, featuring white sidewalls and a grippy brown rubber outsole.

Name: Nike SB Dunk Low Orange Emerald Rise
Description: The Nike Dunk Low SB ‘Orange Emerald Rise’ showcases hairy suede on the upper, featuring a base color in Emerald Rise with contrasting orange overlays at the forefoot and heel. The signature Swoosh appears in aqua blue suede, matching the Nike logo hits that adorn the tongue tag and back tab. The insole packs a Zoom Air unit in the heel for impact protection. Underpinning the sneaker is a durable rubber cupsole in Lemon Chiffon.

Name: Wmns Shox TL 'White Silver' 2023
Description: The 2023 edition of the Nike Women’s Shox TL ‘White Silver’ features a textured white mesh upper fortified with tonal TPU overlays and accented with a molded Swoosh outlined in metallic silver embroidery. Nike Shox branding appears at the tongue and back heel in Max Orange, delivering unexpected pops of color. The silhouette’s unique cushioning system takes the form of a series of polyurethane pillars, supported underfoot by a durable rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Supersonic Light Bone Black
Description: The Nike Air Zoom Vomero 5 ‘Supersonic’ features an airy white mesh upper reinforced with black synthetic leather detailing at the forefoot and heel. Glow-in-the-dark accents make their way to the molded heel counter and quarter-panel cage, overlaid with a signature Swoosh in synthetic white leather. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a full-length Phylon midsole, fitted with Zoom Air cushioning and supported by a glow-in-the-dark rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Dunk Low Cacao Wow (Women's)
Description: The Nike Women’s Dunk Low ‘Cacao Wow’ features smooth leather on the upper, featuring a white base with chocolate brown overlays and a color-matched Swoosh. Traditional Nike branding appears on the tongue tag, back tab and sockliner. A vintage off-white finish is applied to the midsole, fitted with an interior foam wedge and reinforced by a durable brown rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 LX Amber Brown Phantom
Description: The Nike Air Force 1 ‘07 ‘Amber Brown’ utilizes a rosy beige hue on the upper, built with a combination of breathable canvas and tumbled leather. In addition to an ivory-colored suede Swoosh, branding elements include a woven Nike tag atop the tongue and a Nike wordmark embroidered on the back tab. Anchoring the low-top is an off-white rubber cupsole, enhanced with an Air-sole unit encapsulated in a lightweight polyurethane wedge.

Name: Nike Shox TL Black Max Orange (Women's)
Description: The 2023 edition of the Nike Women’s Shox TL ‘Black’ features a sleek black finish on the textile upper, featuring glossy TPU overlays and breathable mesh on the toe box. Max Orange accents land on Nike Shox branding hits at the tongue and heel, while reflective detailing provides enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. The retro runner rides on a series of Shox pillars made with compressible polyurethane.

Name: Nike Ja 1 EYBL Melon Tint
Description: The Nike Ja 1 ‘EYBL’ celebrates Nike’s Elite Youth Basketball League with a colorful rendition of Ja Morant’s debut signature shoe. The upper blends open mesh construction in Melon Tint with tonal synthetic leather overlays and a wraparound TPU Swoosh in a bright purple hue. A multicolor pattern enlivens the heel, marked with an embroidered EYBL logo on the lateral side. The low-top rests on a two-tone Phylon midsole, featuring a Jade Ice finish throughout the forefoot and a solid black heel with speckled detailing. A forefoot Zoom Air unit provides on-court responsiveness.

Name: Nike Calm Slide Geode Teal
Description: The Nike Calm Slide ‘Geode Teal’ brings a vivid finish to a versatile slip-on that marries minimalist style with superior comfort. Rendered in a rich teal hue, the seamless build is crafted from lightweight and quick-drying foam. Nike Swoosh branding decorates the upper and footbed, with the latter featuring a textured top layer designed to hold the foot securely in place. The raised midsole delivers a cushy ride, while the full-length rubber outsole provides durable traction poolside or on the street.

Name: Ja 1 'Fuel'
Description: The Nike Ja 1 ‘Ember Glow’ brings an energetic palette to Ja Morant’s inaugural signature shoe. A bright crimson hue floods the upper, crafted from open-cell mesh with stitched synthetic leather overlays throughout the forefoot. Contrasting hits of color arrive via a blue TPU Swoosh and mismatched lavender and aqua tongue tags, each emblazoned with Ja’s personal logo. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a white Phylon midsole, fitted with a forefoot Zoom Air unit and supported by a durable black rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Dunk Low Chicago Split
Description: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Chicago Split’ showcases an instantly recognizable palette forever linked to the iconic Air Jordan 1. The leather upper features a crisp white base with contrasting overlays in University Red. A split leather Swoosh cuts across the side panel in black and Light Silver. The split-design theme extends to the Nike branding hits on the tongue tag and back tab, celebrating Nike’s past and present. A vintage off-white finish is applied to the midsole, reinforced underfoot by a two-tone rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Dunk Low New Americana Washed Denim
Description: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Washed Denim’ brings an aged workwear aesthetic to the heritage hoops shoe. The low-top carries a white tumbled leather upper, accented with patterned indigo denim on the signature Swoosh and low-cut collar. A woven Nike tag embellishes the cream-colored nylon tongue, while an embroidered Nike wordmark graces the back tab. Underpinning the sneaker is a vintage off-white midsole, supported underfoot by a grippy gum rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Air Force 1 Low West Coast Los Angeles
Description: Dropping as part of the ‘Nike Coast Pack,’ the Nike Air Force 1 Low ‘West Coast’ pays homage to the laid-back culture of Southern California. The classic silhouette features a blue canvas upper with tonal leather detailing on the signature Swoosh and Nike-branded heel tab. Unique details include ‘Nike Coast’ lace jewels, a quilted satin lining, and a woven LA tag on the lateral heel. The low-top is mounted on a white rubber midsole, fitted with an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel and reinforced by a grippy gum rubber outsole.

Name: Nike SB Dunk Low Jarritos
Description: The Jarritos x Nike Dunk Low SB showcases a collaborative design inspired by the popular Mexican soda brand. The upper combines a Phantom white leather base with hemp canvas overlays and a Malachite green textile Swoosh. The Jarritos logo is embroidered in green and orange on the lateral heel, while dual branding embellishes the woven tongue tag. Mismatched heel tabs are emblazoned with 'Nike' and 'Jarritos' across the left and right shoe. Anchoring the sneaker is a durable rubber cupsole that pairs white sidewalls with a two-tone green and orange outsole.

Name: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Breast Cancer Awareness
Description: The PUMA MB.01 ‘Breast Cancer Awareness’ delivers a special-edition colorway released in conjunction with Susan G. Komen, the long-running nonprofit breast cancer organization. LaMelo Ball’s debut signature shoe carries a red engineered mesh upper, fortified with dark pink fused overlays throughout the forefoot. The Komen Foundation’s ribbon logo appears on the tongue tag, while LaMelo’s ‘Not From Here’ tagline is inscribed on the vamp. A matching red finish is applied to a caged NITROFOAM midsole.

Name: Reebok Royal BB4500 Hi White Blue Grey
Description: Royal BB4500 Hi 2 EF7825

Name: Salomon XT-4 OG Notre
Description: The Notre x Salomon XT-4 OG ‘Grass Stained’ presents the Chicago-based retailer’s nostalgic take on the trail running shoe. Inspired by a comfortably worn-in grass-stained shoe, the upper features gradient green accents on a breathable textile upper, fortified with seamless synthetic overlays and secured with Quicklace closure. Dual branding appears on the sockliner, while ‘Notre’ is stamped on the medial heel. Lightweight cushioning arrives via an EVA midsole, supported underfoot by a lugged Contagrip rubber outsole.

Name: Salomon XT-6 Expanse Sandy Liang (Women's)
Description: The Sandy Liang x Salomon XT-6 Expanse ‘Cradle Pink’ made its global debut at the designer’s Fall 2023 runway show during New York Fashion Week. The upper is composed of airy pink mesh with durable white synthetic overlays and a contrasting black toe cap. Emerald accents land on the heel tab and tongue, marked with a discreet floral graphic and Sandy Liang branding. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a full-length EVA midsole, reinforced underfoot by a Mud Contagrip outsole.

Name: END. x Mastermind Japan x Sk8-Hi 'Black'
Description: The END. x Mastermind Japan x Vans Sk8-Hi ‘Black’ is taken from a capsule collection that reimagines the classic silhouette with a rebellious punk-rock sensibility. Mastermind’s signature skull and crossbones graphic is plastered across a black canvas backdrop on the medial side, while the opposite side features black suede construction with zippered closure, an elongated black leather eyestay, and a white leather side stripe. Atop the tongue, a woven Vans tag is accessorized with metal hardware. Anchoring the sneaker is a deconstructed rubber midsole with misaligned paneling. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole reveals Vans’ signature checkerboard print.

Name: Vans Skate Authentic Palace Jeremy the Duck Black
Description: The Palace x Vans Skate Authentic “Jeremy the Duck - Black” is one of three colorways of the low-top skate shoe designed by the London skate and streetwear brand and Vans. A Summer 2021 release, the “Jeremy the Duck” Skate Authentic marries two skate empires together for a long overdue collaboration. Palace’s cheeky “Jeremy the Duck” mascot fuels the design and appears on an all-over print graphic across the black canvas upper. A black-and-white checkerboard product tag appears on the lateral side of the forefoot and white contrast stitching outlines each panel. Dual “Palace” and “Vans” branding is printed on the lateral side of white rubber midsole. Co-branding can also be found on the red license plate on the back of the shoe. Release date: July 2, 2021

Name: Vans Old Skool Velcro Black White
Description: Inspired by the iconic Vans skate shoe, the Old Skool V sports a low profile look in black sturdy canvas and suede uppers. Hook-and-loop strap closures in place of laces make for easy wearing. Other signature details include a classic rubber waffle outsole and a True White side stripe.

Name: Vans Sk8-Hi MTE 2.0 DX Valerian White (Women's)
Description: The Vans Sk8-Hi MTE 2.0 DX “Valerian/True White” is a pair of rugged, water-resistant high-tops from the California-based footwear brand. Vans uses their popular Sk8-Hi model as the inspiration behind a special remaking for inclement weather. The aforementioned water-resistant upper features purple leather eyelets as well as a tonal forefoot and mid-panel. Tonal water-proof suede covers the collar and heel. Vans outfits the durable shoe with their classic white leather jazzy stripe and includes a small branding tag near the collar. The inner is lined with an extra layer of warm to keep things extra cozy on those particularly frigid winter days. Completing the design is a white rubber midsole with a gum traction bottom that assists in conquering snow, slush and anything else that is thrown its way.

Name: Vans Old Skool 36 DX NBHD x Mr. Cartoon
Description: The NEIGHBORHOOD x Mister Cartoon x Vans Old Skool 36 DX ‘Tokyo Los Angeles’ is taken from a two-piece pack made in collaboration with the long-running Japanese streetwear brand and the acclaimed LA-based tattoo artist. The sneaker features a monochromatic black suede upper with tonal leather side stripes and custom ‘Tokyo’ and ‘Los Angeles’ embroidery on the toe box of the right and left shoe. On the back, ‘Uncle Toons Mart’ and ‘By NEIGHBORHOOD’ adorns each heel panel.

Name: Vans Sk8-Hi National Geographic
Description: SK8 Hi ReissueVN0A3TKPXHP

Name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Ararat (2020/2022)
Description: Debuting at London Fashion Week in February 2020, the Yeezy Foam Runner ‘Ararat’ launched without warning the following June through Kanye West’s Yeezy Supply website. The molded slip-on is constructed from a unique foam compound that blends lightweight EVA with harvested algae. Sculpted lines and a neutral monochromatic finish promote a streamlined, futuristic aesthetic, while a series of oval cut-outs enable airflow for ventilated comfort.
